45 bool IsCompressed(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
46  if (!node.valid()) return false;
47  if (selector->is_load(node)) {
48  auto load = selector->load_view(node);
49  return load.loaded_rep().IsCompressed();
50  } else if (const PhiOp* phi = selector->TryCast<PhiOp>(node)) {
51  MachineRepresentation phi_rep = phi->rep.machine_representation();
52  return phi_rep == MachineRepresentation::kCompressed ||
53  phi_rep == MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer;
54  }
55  return false;
56 }
57 
58 #ifdef DEBUG
59 // {left_idx} and {right_idx} are assumed to be the inputs of a commutative
60 // binop. This function checks that {left_idx} is not the only constant input of
61 // this binop (since the graph should have been normalized before, putting
62 // constants on the right input of binops when possible).
63 bool LhsIsNotOnlyConstant(Graph* graph, OpIndex left_idx, OpIndex right_idx) {
64  const Operation& left = graph->Get(left_idx);
65  const Operation& right = graph->Get(right_idx);
66 
67  if (right.Is<ConstantOp>()) {
68  // There is a constant on the right.
69  return true;
70  }
71  if (left.Is<ConstantOp>()) {
72  // Constant on the left but not on the right.
73  return false;
74  }
75 
76  // Left is not a constant
77  return true;
78 }
79 
80 #endif
81 
82 } // namespace

84 // TODO(dmercadier): consider taking a DisplacementMode as input so that we can
85 // be more permissive towards min_int.
86 bool ValueFitsIntoImmediate(int64_t value) {
87  // int32_t min will overflow if displacement mode is kNegativeDisplacement.
88  constexpr int64_t kImmediateMin = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() + 1;
89  constexpr int64_t kImmediateMax = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max();
90  static_assert(kImmediateMin ==
91  LoadStoreSimplificationConfiguration::kMinOffset);
92  static_assert(kImmediateMax ==
93  LoadStoreSimplificationConfiguration::kMaxOffset);
94  return kImmediateMin <= value && value <= kImmediateMax;
95 }
96 
97 bool CanBeImmediate(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
98  // TODO(dmercadier): this is not in sync with GetImmediateIntegerValue, which
99  // is surprising because we often use the pattern
100  // `if (CanBeImmediate()) { GetImmediateIntegerValue }`. We should make sure
101  // that both functions are in sync.
102  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
103  if (!op.Is<ConstantOp>()) return false;
104  const ConstantOp& constant = op.Cast<ConstantOp>();
105  switch (constant.kind) {
106  case ConstantOp::Kind::kCompressedHeapObject: {
107  if (!COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) return false;
108  // For builtin code we need static roots
109  if (selector->isolate()->bootstrapper() && !V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
110  return false;
111  }
112  const RootsTable& roots_table = selector->isolate()->roots_table();
113  RootIndex root_index;
114  Handle<HeapObject> value = constant.handle();
115  if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(value, &root_index)) {
116  return RootsTable::IsReadOnly(root_index);
117  }
118  return false;
119  }
120  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32: {
121  const int32_t value = constant.word32();
122  // int32_t min will overflow if displacement mode is
123  // kNegativeDisplacement.
124  return value != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
125  }
126  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64: {
127  const int64_t value = constant.word64();
128  return ValueFitsIntoImmediate(value);
129  }
130  case ConstantOp::Kind::kSmi: {
131  if (Is64()) {
132  const int64_t value = constant.smi().ptr();
133  return ValueFitsIntoImmediate(value);
134  } else {
135  const int32_t value = constant.smi().ptr();
136  // int32_t min will overflow if displacement mode is
137  // kNegativeDisplacement.
138  return value != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
139  }
140  }
141  case ConstantOp::Kind::kNumber:
142  return constant.number().get_bits() == 0;
143  default:
144  return false;
145  }
146 }
147 
148 int32_t GetImmediateIntegerValue(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
149  DCHECK(CanBeImmediate(selector, node));
150  const ConstantOp& constant = selector->Get(node).Cast<ConstantOp>();
151  switch (constant.kind) {
152  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32:
153  return constant.word32();
154  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64:
155  return static_cast<int32_t>(constant.word64());
156  case ConstantOp::Kind::kSmi:
157  return static_cast<int32_t>(constant.smi().ptr());
158  case ConstantOp::Kind::kNumber:
159  DCHECK_EQ(constant.number().get_bits(), 0);
160  return 0;
161  default:
162  UNREACHABLE();
163  }
164 }
165 
166 struct ScaledIndexMatch {
167  OpIndex base;
168  OpIndex index;
169  int scale;
170 };
171 
172 bool MatchScaledIndex(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
173  OpIndex* index, int* scale, bool* power_of_two_plus_one) {
174  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(index);
175  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(scale);
176 
177  auto MatchScaleConstant = [](const Operation& op, int& scale,
178  bool* plus_one) {
179  const ConstantOp* constant = op.TryCast<ConstantOp>();
180  if (constant == nullptr) return false;
181  if (constant->kind != ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32 &&
182  constant->kind != ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64) {
183  return false;
184  }
185  uint64_t value = constant->integral();
186  if (plus_one) *plus_one = false;
187  if (value == 1) return (scale = 0), true;
188  if (value == 2) return (scale = 1), true;
189  if (value == 4) return (scale = 2), true;
190  if (value == 8) return (scale = 3), true;
191  if (plus_one == nullptr) return false;
192  *plus_one = true;
193  if (value == 3) return (scale = 1), true;
194  if (value == 5) return (scale = 2), true;
195  if (value == 9) return (scale = 3), true;
196  return false;
197  };
198 
199  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
200  if (const WordBinopOp* binop = op.TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
201  if (binop->kind != WordBinopOp::Kind::kMul) return false;
202  if (MatchScaleConstant(selector->Get(binop->right()), *scale,
203  power_of_two_plus_one)) {
204  *index = binop->left();
205  return true;
206  }
207  if (MatchScaleConstant(selector->Get(binop->left()), *scale,
208  power_of_two_plus_one)) {
209  *index = binop->right();
210  return true;
211  }
212  return false;
213  } else if (const ShiftOp* shift = op.TryCast<ShiftOp>()) {
214  if (shift->kind != ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft) return false;
215  int64_t scale_value;
216  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(shift->right(), &scale_value)) {
217  if (scale_value < 0 || scale_value > 3) return false;
218  *index = shift->left();
219  *scale = static_cast<int>(scale_value);
220  if (power_of_two_plus_one) *power_of_two_plus_one = false;
221  return true;
222  }
223  }
224  return false;
225 }
226 
227 std::optional<ScaledIndexMatch> TryMatchScaledIndex(
228  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
229  bool allow_power_of_two_plus_one) {
230  ScaledIndexMatch match;
231  bool plus_one = false;
232  if (MatchScaledIndex(selector, node, &match.index, &match.scale,
233  allow_power_of_two_plus_one ? &plus_one : nullptr)) {
234  match.base = plus_one ? match.index : OpIndex{};
235  return match;
236  }
237  return std::nullopt;
238 }
239 
240 std::optional<ScaledIndexMatch> TryMatchScaledIndex32(
241  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
242  bool allow_power_of_two_plus_one) {
243  return TryMatchScaledIndex(selector, node, allow_power_of_two_plus_one);
244 }
245 
246 std::optional<ScaledIndexMatch> TryMatchScaledIndex64(
247  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
248  bool allow_power_of_two_plus_one) {
249  return TryMatchScaledIndex(selector, node, allow_power_of_two_plus_one);
250 }

252 struct BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch {
253  OpIndex base = {};
254  OpIndex index = {};
255  int scale = 0;
256  int64_t displacement = 0;
257  DisplacementMode displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
258 };
259 
260 std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch>
261 TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64ForWordBinop(
262  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex left, OpIndex right,
263  bool is_commutative);
264 
265 std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch>
266 TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(InstructionSelector* selector,
267  OpIndex node) {
268  // The BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher canonicalizes the order of
269  // displacements and scale factors that are used as inputs, so instead of
270  // enumerating all possible patterns by brute force, checking for node
271  // clusters using the following templates in the following order suffices
272  // to find all of the interesting cases (S = index * scale, B = base
273  // input, D = displacement input):
274  //
275  // (S + (B + D))
276  // (S + (B + B))
277  // (S + D)
278  // (S + B)
279  // ((S + D) + B)
280  // ((S + B) + D)
281  // ((B + D) + B)
282  // ((B + B) + D)
283  // (B + D)
284  // (B + B)
285  BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch result;
286  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
287 
288  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
289  if (const LoadOp* load = op.TryCast<LoadOp>()) {
290  result.base = load->base();
291  result.index = load->index().value_or_invalid();
292  result.scale = load->element_size_log2;
293  result.displacement = load->offset;
294  if (load->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
295  return result;
296  } else if (const StoreOp* store = op.TryCast<StoreOp>()) {
297  result.base = store->base();
298  result.index = store->index().value_or_invalid();
299  result.scale = store->element_size_log2;
300  result.displacement = store->offset;
301  if (store->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
302  return result;
303  } else if (op.Is<WordBinopOp>()) {
304  // Nothing to do here, fall into the case below.
305 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
306  } else if (const Simd128LaneMemoryOp* lane_op =
307  op.TryCast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>()) {
308  result.base = lane_op->base();
309  result.index = lane_op->index();
310  result.scale = 0;
311  result.displacement = 0;
312  if (lane_op->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
313  return result;
314  } else if (const Simd128LoadTransformOp* load_transform_128 =
315  op.TryCast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>()) {
316  result.base = load_transform_128->base();
317  DCHECK_EQ(load_transform_128->offset, 0);
318 
319  if (CanBeImmediate(selector, load_transform_128->index())) {
320  result.index = {};
321  result.displacement =
322  GetImmediateIntegerValue(selector, load_transform_128->index());
323  } else {
324  result.index = load_transform_128->index();
325  result.displacement = 0;
326  }
327 
328  result.scale = 0;
329  DCHECK(!load_transform_128->load_kind.tagged_base);
330  return result;
331 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
332  } else if (const Simd256LoadTransformOp* load_transform_256 =
333  op.TryCast<Simd256LoadTransformOp>()) {
334  result.base = load_transform_256->base();
335  result.index = load_transform_256->index();
336  DCHECK_EQ(load_transform_256->offset, 0);
337  result.scale = 0;
338  result.displacement = 0;
339  DCHECK(!load_transform_256->load_kind.tagged_base);
340  return result;
341 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
342 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
343  } else {
344  return std::nullopt;
345  }
346 
347  const WordBinopOp& binop = op.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
348  OpIndex left = binop.left();
349  OpIndex right = binop.right();
350  return TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64ForWordBinop(
351  selector, left, right, binop.IsCommutative());
352 }
353 
354 std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch>
355 TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64ForWordBinop(
356  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex left, OpIndex right,
357  bool is_commutative) {
358  // In the comments of this function, the following letters have the following
359  // meaning:
360  //
361  // S: scaled index. That is, "OpIndex * constant" or "OpIndex << constant",
362  // where "constant" is a small power of 2 (1, 2, 4, 8 for the
363  // multiplication, 0, 1, 2 or 3 for the shift). The "constant" is called
364  // "scale" in the BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch struct that is
365  // returned.
366  //
367  // B: base. Just a regular OpIndex.
368  //
369  // D: displacement. An integral constant.
370 
371  // Helper to check (S + ...)
372  auto match_S_plus = [&selector](OpIndex left, OpIndex right)
373  -> std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch> {
374  BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch result;
375  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
376 
377  // Check (S + ...)
378  if (MatchScaledIndex(selector, left, &result.index, &result.scale,
379  nullptr)) {
380  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
381 
382  // Check (S + (... binop ...))
383  if (const WordBinopOp* right_binop =
384  selector->Get(right).TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
385  // Check (S + (B - D))
386  if (right_binop->kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub) {
387  if (!selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right_binop->right(),
388  &result.displacement)) {
389  return std::nullopt;
390  }
391  result.base = right_binop->left();
392  result.displacement_mode = kNegativeDisplacement;
393  return result;
394  }
395  // Check (S + (... + ...))
396  if (right_binop->kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd) {
397  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right_binop->right(),
398  &result.displacement)) {
399  // (S + (B + D))
400  result.base = right_binop->left();
401  } else if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(
402  right_binop->left(), &result.displacement)) {
403  // (S + (D + B))
404  result.base = right_binop->right();
405  } else {
406  // Treat it as (S + B)
407  result.base = right;
408  result.displacement = 0;
409  }
410  return result;
411  }
412  }
413 
414  // Check (S + D)
415  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right, &result.displacement)) {
416  result.base = OpIndex{};
417  return result;
418  }
419 
420  // Treat it as (S + B)
421  result.base = right;
422  result.displacement = 0;
423  return result;
424  }
425 
426  return std::nullopt;
427  };
428 
429  // Helper to check ((S + ...) + ...)
430  auto match_S_plus_plus = [&selector](OpIndex left, OpIndex right,
431  OpIndex left_add_left,
432  OpIndex left_add_right)
433  -> std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch> {
434  DCHECK_EQ(selector->Get(left).Cast<WordBinopOp>().kind,
435  WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd);
436 
437  BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch result;
438  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
439 
440  if (MatchScaledIndex(selector, left_add_left, &result.index, &result.scale,
441  nullptr)) {
442  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
443  // Check ((S + D) + B)
444  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(left_add_right,
445  &result.displacement)) {
446  result.base = right;
447  return result;
448  }
449  // Check ((S + B) + D)
450  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right, &result.displacement)) {
451  result.base = left_add_right;
452  return result;
453  }
454  // Treat it as (B + B) and use index as right B.
455  result.base = left;
456  result.index = right;
457  result.scale = 0;
458  DCHECK_EQ(result.displacement, 0);
459  return result;
460  }
461  return std::nullopt;
462  };
463 
464  // Helper to check ((... + ...) + ...)
465  auto match_plus_plus = [&selector, &match_S_plus_plus](OpIndex left,
466  OpIndex right)
467  -> std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch> {
468  BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch result;
469  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
470 
471  // Check ((... + ...) + ...)
472  if (const WordBinopOp* left_add =
473  selector->Get(left).TryCast<WordBinopOp>();
474  left_add && left_add->kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd) {
475  // Check ((S + ...) + ...)
476  auto maybe_res =
477  match_S_plus_plus(left, right, left_add->left(), left_add->right());
478  if (maybe_res) return maybe_res;
479  // Check ((... + S) + ...)
480  maybe_res =
481  match_S_plus_plus(left, right, left_add->right(), left_add->left());
482  if (maybe_res) return maybe_res;
483  }
484 
485  return std::nullopt;
486  };
487 
488  // Check (S + ...)
489  auto maybe_res = match_S_plus(left, right);
490  if (maybe_res) return maybe_res;
491 
492  if (is_commutative) {
493  // Check (... + S)
494  maybe_res = match_S_plus(right, left);
495  if (maybe_res) {
496  return maybe_res;
497  }
498  }
499 
500  // Check ((... + ...) + ...)
501  maybe_res = match_plus_plus(left, right);
502  if (maybe_res) return maybe_res;
503 
504  if (is_commutative) {
505  // Check (... + (... + ...))
506  maybe_res = match_plus_plus(right, left);
507  if (maybe_res) {
508  return maybe_res;
509  }
510  }
511 
512  BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch result;
513  result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
514 
515  // Check (B + D)
516  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(right, &result.displacement)) {
517  result.base = left;
518  return result;
519  }
520 
521  // Treat as (B + B) and use index as left B.
522  result.index = left;
523  result.base = right;
524  return result;
525 }
526 
527 std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch>
528 TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement32(InstructionSelector* selector,
529  OpIndex node) {
530  return TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(selector, node);
531 }

533 // Adds X64-specific methods for generating operands.
534 class X64OperandGenerator final : public OperandGenerator {
535  public:
536  explicit X64OperandGenerator(InstructionSelector* selector)
537  : OperandGenerator(selector) {}
538 
539  bool CanBeImmediate(OpIndex node) {
540  return compiler::CanBeImmediate(this->selector(), node);
541  }
542 
543  int32_t GetImmediateIntegerValue(OpIndex node) {
544  return compiler::GetImmediateIntegerValue(this->selector(), node);
545  }
546 
547  bool CanBeMemoryOperand(InstructionCode opcode, OpIndex node, OpIndex input,
548  int effect_level) {
549  if (!selector()->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(input)) return false;
550  if (!selector()->CanCover(node, input)) return false;
551 
552  if (effect_level != selector()->GetEffectLevel(input)) {
553  return false;
554  }
555 
556  MachineRepresentation rep =
557  selector()->load_view(input).loaded_rep().representation();
558  switch (opcode) {
559  case kX64And:
560  case kX64Or:
561  case kX64Xor:
562  case kX64Add:
563  case kX64Sub:
564  case kX64Push:
565  case kX64Cmp:
566  case kX64Test:
567  // When pointer compression is enabled 64-bit memory operands can't be
568  // used for tagged values.
569  return rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord64 ||
570  (!COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && IsAnyTagged(rep));
571  case kX64And32:
572  case kX64Or32:
573  case kX64Xor32:
574  case kX64Add32:
575  case kX64Sub32:
576  case kX64Cmp32:
577  case kX64Test32:
578  // When pointer compression is enabled 32-bit memory operands can be
579  // used for tagged values.
580  return rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32 ||
581  (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL &&
582  (IsAnyTagged(rep) || IsAnyCompressed(rep)));
583  case kAVXFloat64Add:
584  case kAVXFloat64Sub:
585  case kAVXFloat64Mul:
586  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, rep);
587  return true;
588  case kAVXFloat32Add:
589  case kAVXFloat32Sub:
590  case kAVXFloat32Mul:
591  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kFloat32, rep);
592  return true;
593  case kX64Cmp16:
594  case kX64Test16:
595  return rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16;
596  case kX64Cmp8:
597  case kX64Test8:
598  return rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8;
599  default:
600  break;
601  }
602  return false;
603  }
604 
605  bool IsZeroIntConstant(OpIndex node) const {
606  if (const ConstantOp* op = selector()->TryCast<ConstantOp>(node)) {
607  switch (op->kind) {
608  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32:
609  return op->word32() == 0;
610  case ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64:
611  return op->word64() == 0;
612  default:
613  break;
614  }
615  }
616  return false;
617  }
618 
619  AddressingMode GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
620  OptionalOpIndex index, int scale_exponent, OpIndex base,
621  int64_t displacement, DisplacementMode displacement_mode,
622  InstructionOperand inputs[], size_t* input_count,
623  RegisterUseKind reg_kind = RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister) {
624  AddressingMode mode = kMode_MRI;
625  OpIndex base_before_folding = base;
626  bool fold_base_into_displacement = false;
627  int64_t fold_value = 0;
628  if (base.valid() && (index.valid() || displacement != 0)) {
629  if (CanBeImmediate(base) && index.valid() &&
630  ValueFitsIntoImmediate(displacement)) {
631  fold_value = GetImmediateIntegerValue(base);
632  if (displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement) {
633  fold_value -= displacement;
634  } else {
635  fold_value += displacement;
636  }
637  if (V8_UNLIKELY(fold_value == 0)) {
638  base = OpIndex{};
639  displacement = 0;
640  } else if (ValueFitsIntoImmediate(fold_value)) {
641  base = OpIndex{};
642  fold_base_into_displacement = true;
643  }
644  } else if (IsZeroIntConstant(base)) {
645  base = OpIndex{};
646  }
647  }
648  if (base.valid()) {
649  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(base, reg_kind);
650  if (index.valid()) {
651  DCHECK(scale_exponent >= 0 && scale_exponent <= 3);
652  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(index.value(), reg_kind);
653  if (displacement != 0) {
654  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate64(
655  displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
656  : displacement);
657  static const AddressingMode kMRnI_modes[] = {kMode_MR1I, kMode_MR2I,
658  kMode_MR4I, kMode_MR8I};
659  mode = kMRnI_modes[scale_exponent];
660  } else {
661  static const AddressingMode kMRn_modes[] = {kMode_MR1, kMode_MR2,
662  kMode_MR4, kMode_MR8};
663  mode = kMRn_modes[scale_exponent];
664  }
665  } else {
666  if (displacement == 0) {
667  mode = kMode_MR;
668  } else {
669  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate64(
670  displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
671  : displacement);
672  mode = kMode_MRI;
673  }
674  }
675  } else {
676  DCHECK(scale_exponent >= 0 && scale_exponent <= 3);
677  if (fold_base_into_displacement) {
678  DCHECK(!base.valid());
679  DCHECK(index.valid());
680  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(index.value(), reg_kind);
681  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(fold_value));
682  static const AddressingMode kMnI_modes[] = {kMode_MRI, kMode_M2I,
683  kMode_M4I, kMode_M8I};
684  mode = kMnI_modes[scale_exponent];
685  } else if (displacement != 0) {
686  if (!index.valid()) {
687  // This seems to only occur in (0 + k) cases, but we don't have an
688  // addressing mode for a simple constant, so we use the base in a
689  // register for kMode_MRI.
690  CHECK(IsZeroIntConstant(base_before_folding));
691  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(base_before_folding, reg_kind);
692  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate64(
693  displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
694  : displacement);
695  mode = kMode_MRI;
696  } else {
697  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(index.value(), reg_kind);
698  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate64(
699  displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
700  : displacement);
701  static const AddressingMode kMnI_modes[] = {kMode_MRI, kMode_M2I,
702  kMode_M4I, kMode_M8I};
703  mode = kMnI_modes[scale_exponent];
704  }
705  } else {
706  DCHECK(index.valid());
707  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(index.value(), reg_kind);
708  static const AddressingMode kMn_modes[] = {kMode_MR, kMode_MR1,
709  kMode_M4, kMode_M8};
710  mode = kMn_modes[scale_exponent];
711  if (mode == kMode_MR1) {
712  // [%r1 + %r1*1] has a smaller encoding than [%r1*2+0]
713  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(index.value(), reg_kind);
714  }
715  }
716  }
717  return mode;
718  }
719 
720  AddressingMode GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
721  OpIndex operand, InstructionOperand inputs[], size_t* input_count,
722  RegisterUseKind reg_kind = RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister);
723 
724  InstructionOperand GetEffectiveIndexOperand(OpIndex index,
725  AddressingMode* mode) {
726  if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
727  *mode = kMode_MRI;
728  return UseImmediate(index);
729  } else {
730  *mode = kMode_MR1;
731  return UseUniqueRegister(index);
732  }
733  }
734 
735  bool CanBeBetterLeftOperand(OpIndex node) const {
736  return !selector()->IsReallyLive(node);
737  }
738 };
739 
740 namespace {
741 
742 struct LoadStoreView {
743  explicit LoadStoreView(const Operation& op) {
744  DCHECK(op.Is<LoadOp>() || op.Is<StoreOp>());
745  if (const LoadOp* load = op.TryCast<LoadOp>()) {
746  base = load->base();
747  index = load->index();
748  offset = load->offset;
749  } else {
750  DCHECK(op.Is<StoreOp>());
751  const StoreOp& store = op.Cast<StoreOp>();
752  base = store.base();
753  index = store.index();
754  offset = store.offset;
755  }
756  }
757  OpIndex base;
758  OptionalOpIndex index;
759  int32_t offset;
760 };
761 
762 } // namespace
763 
764 AddressingMode X64OperandGenerator::GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
765  OpIndex operand, InstructionOperand inputs[], size_t* input_count,
766  RegisterUseKind reg_kind) {
767  const Operation& op = Get(operand);
768  if (op.Is<LoadOp>() || op.Is<StoreOp>()) {
769  LoadStoreView load_or_store(op);
770  if (ExternalReference reference;
771  MatchExternalConstant(load_or_store.base, &reference) &&
772  !load_or_store.index.valid()) {
773  if (selector()->CanAddressRelativeToRootsRegister(reference)) {
774  const ptrdiff_t delta =
775  load_or_store.offset +
776  MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(
777  selector()->isolate(), reference);
778  if (is_int32(delta)) {
779  inputs[(*input_count)++] = TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
780  return kMode_Root;
781  }
782  }
783  }
784  }
785 
786  auto m = TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(selector(), operand);
787  DCHECK(m.has_value());
788  if (IsCompressed(selector(), m->base)) {
789  DCHECK(!m->index.valid());
790  DCHECK(m->displacement == 0 || ValueFitsIntoImmediate(m->displacement));
791  AddressingMode mode = kMode_MCR;
792  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(m->base, reg_kind);
793  if (m->displacement != 0) {
794  inputs[(*input_count)++] =
795  m->displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement
796  ? UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(-m->displacement))
797  : UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(m->displacement));
798  mode = kMode_MCRI;
799  }
800  return mode;
801  }
802  if (m->base.valid() && selector()->Get(m->base).Is<LoadRootRegisterOp>() &&
803  !m->index.valid()) {
804  DCHECK_EQ(m->scale, 0);
805  DCHECK(ValueFitsIntoImmediate(m->displacement));
806  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(m->displacement));
807  return kMode_Root;
808  } else if (ValueFitsIntoImmediate(m->displacement)) {
809  return GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(m->index, m->scale, m->base,
810  m->displacement, m->displacement_mode,
811  inputs, input_count, reg_kind);
812  } else if (!m->base.valid() &&
813  m->displacement_mode == kPositiveDisplacement) {
814  // The displacement cannot be an immediate, but we can use the
815  // displacement as base instead and still benefit from addressing
816  // modes for the scale.
817  UNIMPLEMENTED();
818  } else {
819  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Turn this into a `DCHECK` once we have some
820  // coverage.
821  CHECK_EQ(m->displacement, 0);
822  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(m->base, reg_kind);
823  inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(m->index, reg_kind);
824  return kMode_MR1;
825  }
826 }
827 
828 namespace {
829 
830 ArchOpcode GetLoadOpcode(MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep,
831  RegisterRepresentation result_rep) {
832  // NOTE: The meaning of `loaded_rep` = `MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged()` is
833  // we are loading a compressed tagged field, while `result_rep` =
834  // `RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()` refers to an uncompressed tagged value.
835  switch (loaded_rep) {
836  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
837  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
838  return kX64Movsxbl;
839  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
840  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
841  return kX64Movzxbl;
842  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
843  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
844  return kX64Movsxwl;
845  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
846  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
847  return kX64Movzxwl;
848  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
849  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
850  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
851  return kX64Movl;
852  case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
853  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
854  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
855  return kX64Movq;
856  case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
857  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float32());
858  return kX64Movsh;
859  case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
860  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float32());
861  return kX64Movss;
862  case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
863  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
864  return kX64Movsd;
865 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
866  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
867  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
868  if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
869  return kX64Movl;
870  }
871  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
872  return kX64MovqDecompressTagged;
873  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
874  if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
875  return kX64Movl;
876  }
877  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
878  return kX64MovqDecompressTaggedSigned;
879 #else
880  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
881  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
882  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
883  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
884  return kX64Movq;
885 #endif
886  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
887  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
888  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
889  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
890  return kX64Movq;
891  case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
892  CHECK(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
893  return kX64MovqDecompressProtected;
894  case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
895  UNREACHABLE();
896  case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
897  return kX64MovqDecodeSandboxedPointer;
898  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128():
899  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Simd128());
900  return kX64Movdqu;
901  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
902  DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Simd256());
903  return kX64Movdqu256;
904  }
905 }
906 
907 ArchOpcode GetLoadOpcode(LoadRepresentation load_rep) {
908  ArchOpcode opcode;
909  switch (load_rep.representation()) {
910  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
911  opcode = kX64Movsh;
912  break;
913  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
914  opcode = kX64Movss;
915  break;
916  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
917  opcode = kX64Movsd;
918  break;
919  case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
920  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
921  opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kX64Movsxbl : kX64Movzxbl;
922  break;
923  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
924  opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kX64Movsxwl : kX64Movzxwl;
925  break;
926  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
927  opcode = kX64Movl;
928  break;
929  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
930  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
931 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
932  opcode = kX64Movl;
933  break;
934 #else
935  UNREACHABLE();
936 #endif
937 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
938  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
939  opcode = kX64MovqDecompressTaggedSigned;
940  break;
941  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
942  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
943  opcode = kX64MovqDecompressTagged;
944  break;
945 #else
946  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
947  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
948  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged: // Fall through.
949 #endif
950  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
951  opcode = kX64Movq;
952  break;
953  case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer:
954  CHECK(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
955  opcode = kX64MovqDecompressProtected;
956  break;
957  case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer:
958  opcode = kX64MovqDecodeSandboxedPointer;
959  break;
960  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
961  opcode = kX64Movdqu;
962  break;
963  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: // Fall through.
964  opcode = kX64Movdqu256;
965  break;
966  case MachineRepresentation::kNone: // Fall through.
967  case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord: // Fall through.
968  case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer: // Fall through.
969  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16RawBits:
970  UNREACHABLE();
971  }
972  return opcode;
973 }
974 
975 ArchOpcode GetStoreOpcode(MemoryRepresentation stored_rep) {
976  switch (stored_rep) {
977  case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
978  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
979  return kX64Movb;
980  case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
981  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
982  return kX64Movw;
983  case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
984  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
985  return kX64Movl;
986  case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
987  case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
988  return kX64Movq;
989  case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
990  return kX64Movsh;
991  case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
992  return kX64Movss;
993  case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
994  return kX64Movsd;
995  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
996  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
997  case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
998  return kX64MovqCompressTagged;
999  case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
1000  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
1001  case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
1002  return kX64Movq;
1003  case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
1004  // We never store directly to protected pointers from generated code.
1005  UNREACHABLE();
1006  case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
1007  return kX64MovqStoreIndirectPointer;
1008  case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
1009  return kX64MovqEncodeSandboxedPointer;
1010  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128():
1011  return kX64Movdqu;
1012  case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
1013  return kX64Movdqu256;
1014  }
1015 }
1016 
1017 ArchOpcode GetSeqCstStoreOpcode(StoreRepresentation store_rep) {
1018  switch (store_rep.representation()) {
1019  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
1020  return kAtomicStoreWord8;
1021  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
1022  return kAtomicStoreWord16;
1023  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1024  return kAtomicStoreWord32;
1025  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1026  return kX64Word64AtomicStoreWord64;
1027  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
1028  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
1029  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
1030  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) return kAtomicStoreWord32;
1031  return kX64Word64AtomicStoreWord64;
1032  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
1033  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
1034  CHECK(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
1035  return kAtomicStoreWord32;
1036  default:
1037  UNREACHABLE();
1038  }
1039 }
1040 
1041 // Used for pmin/pmax and relaxed min/max.
1042 template <VectorLength vec_len>
1043 void VisitMinOrMax(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1044  ArchOpcode opcode, bool flip_inputs) {
1045  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1046  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
1047  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
1048  InstructionOperand dst = selector->IsSupported(AVX)
1049  ? g.DefineAsRegister(node)
1050  : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
1051  InstructionCode instr_code = opcode | VectorLengthField::encode(vec_len);
1052  if (flip_inputs) {
1053  // Due to the way minps/minpd work, we want the dst to be same as the second
1054  // input: b = pmin(a, b) directly maps to minps b a.
1055  selector->Emit(instr_code, dst, g.UseRegister(op.input(1)),
1056  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
1057  } else {
1058  selector->Emit(instr_code, dst, g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
1059  g.UseRegister(op.input(1)));
1060  }
1061 }
1062 } // namespace

1064 void InstructionSelector::VisitTraceInstruction(OpIndex node) {
1065  // Currently not used by Turboshaft.
1066  UNIMPLEMENTED();
1067 }

1069 void InstructionSelector::VisitStackSlot(OpIndex node) {
1070  const StackSlotOp& stack_slot = Cast<StackSlotOp>(node);
1071  int slot = frame_->AllocateSpillSlot(stack_slot.size, stack_slot.alignment,
1072  stack_slot.is_tagged);
1073  OperandGenerator g(this);
1074 
1075  Emit(kArchStackSlot, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1076  sequence()->AddImmediate(Constant(slot)), 0, nullptr);
1077 }

1079 void InstructionSelector::VisitAbortCSADcheck(OpIndex node) {
1080  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1081  const AbortCSADcheckOp& check = Cast<AbortCSADcheckOp>(node);
1082  DCHECK_EQ(check.input_count, 1);
1083  Emit(kArchAbortCSADcheck, g.NoOutput(), g.UseFixed(check.message(), rdx));
1084 }

1086 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1087 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoadLane(OpIndex node) {
1088  const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& load = this->Get(node).Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>();
1089  InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
1090  switch (load.lane_kind) {
1091  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8:
1092  opcode = kX64Pinsrb;
1093  break;
1094  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16:
1095  opcode = kX64Pinsrw;
1096  break;
1097  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32:
1098  opcode = kX64Pinsrd;
1099  break;
1100  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64:
1101  opcode = kX64Pinsrq;
1102  break;
1103  }
1104 
1105  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1106  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
1107  // Input 0 is value node, 1 is lane idx, and GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand
1108  // uses up to 3 inputs. This ordering is consistent with other operations that
1109  // use the same opcode.
1110  InstructionOperand inputs[5];
1111  size_t input_count = 0;
1112 
1113  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(load.value());
1114  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(load.lane);
1115 
1116  AddressingMode mode =
1117  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
1118  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
1119 
1120  DCHECK_GE(5, input_count);
1121 
1122  // x64 supports unaligned loads.
1123  DCHECK(!load.kind.maybe_unaligned);
1124  if (load.kind.with_trap_handler) {
1125  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1126  }
1127  Emit(opcode, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs);
1128 }
1129 
1130 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoadTransform(OpIndex node) {
1131  const Simd128LoadTransformOp& op =
1132  this->Get(node).Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>();
1133  ArchOpcode opcode;
1134  switch (op.transform_kind) {
1135  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8S:
1136  opcode = kX64S128Load8x8S;
1137  break;
1138  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8U:
1139  opcode = kX64S128Load8x8U;
1140  break;
1141  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4S:
1142  opcode = kX64S128Load16x4S;
1143  break;
1144  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4U:
1145  opcode = kX64S128Load16x4U;
1146  break;
1147  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2S:
1148  opcode = kX64S128Load32x2S;
1149  break;
1150  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2U:
1151  opcode = kX64S128Load32x2U;
1152  break;
1153  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8Splat:
1154  opcode = kX64S128Load8Splat;
1155  break;
1156  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16Splat:
1157  opcode = kX64S128Load16Splat;
1158  break;
1159  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Splat:
1160  opcode = kX64S128Load32Splat;
1161  break;
1162  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Splat:
1163  opcode = kX64S128Load64Splat;
1164  break;
1165  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Zero:
1166  opcode = kX64Movss;
1167  break;
1168  case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Zero:
1169  opcode = kX64Movsd;
1170  break;
1171  }
1172 
1173  // x64 supports unaligned loads
1174  DCHECK(!op.load_kind.maybe_unaligned);
1175  InstructionCode code = opcode;
1176  if (op.load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
1177  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1178  }
1179  VisitLoad(node, node, code);
1180 }
1181 
1182 #if V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC
1183 void InstructionSelector::VisitS256Const(OpIndex node) {
1184  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1185  static const int kUint32Immediates = kSimd256Size / sizeof(uint32_t);
1186  uint32_t val[kUint32Immediates];
1187  const Simd256ConstantOp& constant = Cast<Simd256ConstantOp>(node);
1188  memcpy(val, constant.value, kSimd256Size);
1189  // If all bytes are zeros or ones, avoid emitting code for generic constants
1190  bool all_zeros = std::all_of(std::begin(val), std::end(val),
1191  [](uint32_t v) { return v == 0; });
1192  // It's should not happen for Turboshaft, IsZero is checked earlier in
1193  // instruction selector
1194  DCHECK(!all_zeros);
1195  bool all_ones = std::all_of(std::begin(val), std::end(val),
1196  [](uint32_t v) { return v == UINT32_MAX; });
1197  InstructionOperand dst = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1198  if (all_zeros) {
1199  Emit(kX64SZero | VectorLengthField::encode(kV256), dst);
1200  } else if (all_ones) {
1201  Emit(kX64SAllOnes | VectorLengthField::encode(kV256), dst);
1202  } else {
1203  Emit(kX64S256Const, dst, g.UseImmediate(val[0]), g.UseImmediate(val[1]),
1204  g.UseImmediate(val[2]), g.UseImmediate(val[3]), g.UseImmediate(val[4]),
1205  g.UseImmediate(val[5]), g.UseImmediate(val[6]),
1206  g.UseImmediate(val[7]));
1207  }
1208 }
1209

1212  Emit(kX64SZero | VectorLengthField::encode(kV256), g.DefineAsRegister(node));

1215 void InstructionSelector::VisitSimd256LoadTransform(OpIndex node) {
1216  const Simd256LoadTransformOp& op =
1217  this->Get(node).Cast<Simd256LoadTransformOp>();
1218  ArchOpcode opcode;
1219  switch (op.transform_kind) {
1220  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x16S:
1221  opcode = kX64S256Load8x16S;
1222  break;
1223  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x16U:
1224  opcode = kX64S256Load8x16U;
1225  break;
1226  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8U:
1227  opcode = kX64S256Load8x8U;
1228  break;
1229  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x8S:
1230  opcode = kX64S256Load16x8S;
1231  break;
1232  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x8U:
1233  opcode = kX64S256Load16x8U;
1234  break;
1235  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x4S:
1236  opcode = kX64S256Load32x4S;
1237  break;
1238  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x4U:
1239  opcode = kX64S256Load32x4U;
1240  break;
1241  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8Splat:
1242  opcode = kX64S256Load8Splat;
1243  break;
1244  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16Splat:
1245  opcode = kX64S256Load16Splat;
1246  break;
1247  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Splat:
1248  opcode = kX64S256Load32Splat;
1249  break;
1250  case Simd256LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Splat:
1251  opcode = kX64S256Load64Splat;
1252  break;
1253  }
1254 
1255  // x64 supports unaligned loads
1256  DCHECK(!op.load_kind.maybe_unaligned);
1257  InstructionCode code = opcode;
1258  if (op.load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
1259  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1260  }
1261  VisitLoad(node, node, code);
1262 }

1302 void InstructionSelector::VisitSimd256Unpack(OpIndex node) {

1323 void InstructionSelector::VisitSimdPack128To256(OpIndex node) {

1345 
1346 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoad(OpIndex node, OpIndex value,
1347  InstructionCode opcode) {
1348  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1349 #ifdef V8_IS_TSAN
1350  // On TSAN builds we require one scratch register. Because of this we also
1351  // have to modify the inputs to take into account possible aliasing and use
1352  // UseUniqueRegister which is not required for non-TSAN builds.
1353  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
1354  size_t temp_count = arraysize(temps);
1355  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister;
1356 #else
1357  InstructionOperand* temps = nullptr;
1358  size_t temp_count = 0;
1359  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister;
1360 #endif // V8_IS_TSAN
1361  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
1362  InstructionOperand inputs[3];
1363  size_t input_count = 0;
1364  AddressingMode mode =
1365  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(value, inputs, &input_count, reg_kind);
1366  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
1367  if (this->is_load(node)) {
1368  auto load = load_view(node);
1369  bool traps_on_null;
1370  if (load.is_protected(&traps_on_null)) {
1371  if (traps_on_null) {
1372  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference);
1373  } else {
1374  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1375  }
1376  }
1377  }
1378  Emit(code, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
1379 }
1380 
1381 void InstructionSelector::VisitLoad(OpIndex node) {
1382  LoadView view = load_view(node);
1383  VisitLoad(node, node,
1384  GetLoadOpcode(view.ts_loaded_rep(), view.ts_result_rep()));
1385 }

1387 void InstructionSelector::VisitProtectedLoad(OpIndex node) { VisitLoad(node); }

1391 // Shared routine for Word32/Word64 Atomic Exchange
1392 void VisitAtomicExchange(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1393  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
1394  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
1395  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
1396  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1397  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1398  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
1399  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.value()),
1400  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.base()),
1401  g.GetEffectiveIndexOperand(atomic_op.index(), &addressing_mode)};
1402  base::SmallVector<InstructionOperand, 3> temps;
1403  if (opcode == kAtomicExchangeWithWriteBarrier) {
1404  temps.push_back(g.TempRegister());
1405  temps.push_back(g.TempRegister());
1406  temps.push_back(g.TempRegister());
1407  }
1408  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)};
1409  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
1410  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
1411  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
1412  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1413  }
1414  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
1415  temps.size(), temps.data());
1416 }
1417 
1418 void VisitStoreCommon(InstructionSelector* selector,
1419  const InstructionSelector::StoreView& store) {
1420  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1421  OpIndex base = store.base();
1422  OptionalOpIndex index = store.index();
1423  OpIndex value = store.value();
1424  int32_t displacement = store.displacement();
1425  uint8_t element_size_log2 = store.element_size_log2();
1426  std::optional<AtomicMemoryOrder> atomic_order = store.memory_order();
1427  MemoryAccessKind acs_kind = store.access_kind();
1428 
1429  const StoreRepresentation store_rep = store.stored_rep();
1430  DCHECK_NE(store_rep.representation(), MachineRepresentation::kMapWord);
1431  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = store_rep.write_barrier_kind();
1432  const bool is_seqcst =
1433  atomic_order && *atomic_order == AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst;
1434 
1435  if (v8_flags.enable_unconditional_write_barriers &&
1436  CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(store_rep.representation())) {
1437  write_barrier_kind = kFullWriteBarrier;
1438  }
1439 
1440  const auto access_mode =
1441  acs_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler
1442  ? (store.is_store_trap_on_null()
1443  ? kMemoryAccessProtectedNullDereference
1444  : MemoryAccessMode::kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds)
1445  : MemoryAccessMode::kMemoryAccessDirect;
1446 
1447  if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
1448  !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1449  DCHECK(
1450  CanBeTaggedOrCompressedOrIndirectPointer(store_rep.representation()));
1451  // Uncompressed stores should not happen if we need a write barrier.
1452  CHECK((store.ts_stored_rep() !=
1453  MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged()) &&
1454  (store.ts_stored_rep() !=
1455  MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer()) &&
1456  (store.ts_stored_rep() !=
1457  MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer()));
1458  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1459  InstructionOperand inputs[5];
1460  size_t input_count = 0;
1461  addressing_mode = g.GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
1462  index, element_size_log2, base, displacement,
1463  DisplacementMode::kPositiveDisplacement, inputs, &input_count,
1464  X64OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister);
1465  DCHECK_LT(input_count, 4);
1466  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
1467  RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
1468  WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
1469  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
1470  InstructionCode code;
1471  if (store_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer) {
1472  DCHECK_EQ(write_barrier_kind, kIndirectPointerWriteBarrier);
1473  // In this case we need to add the IndirectPointerTag as additional input.
1474  code = kArchStoreIndirectWithWriteBarrier;
1475  IndirectPointerTag tag = store.indirect_pointer_tag();
1476  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate64(static_cast<int64_t>(tag));
1477  } else {
1478  code = is_seqcst ? kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier
1479  : kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1480  }
1481  code |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1482  code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1483  code |= AccessModeField::encode(access_mode);
1484  selector->Emit(code, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, arraysize(temps),
1485  temps);
1486  } else {
1487 #ifdef V8_IS_TSAN
1488  // On TSAN builds we require two scratch registers. Because of this we also
1489  // have to modify the inputs to take into account possible aliasing and use
1490  // UseUniqueRegister which is not required for non-TSAN builds.
1491  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
1492  size_t temp_count = arraysize(temps);
1493  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister;
1494 #else
1495  InstructionOperand* temps = nullptr;
1496  size_t temp_count = 0;
1497  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister;
1498 #endif // V8_IS_TSAN
1499 
1500  // Release and non-atomic stores emit MOV and sequentially consistent stores
1501  // emit XCHG.
1502  // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
1503 
1504  ArchOpcode opcode;
1505  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1506  InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1507  size_t input_count = 0;
1508 
1509  if (is_seqcst) {
1510  // SeqCst stores emit XCHG instead of MOV, so encode the inputs as we
1511  // would for XCHG. XCHG can't encode the value as an immediate and has
1512  // fewer addressing modes available.
1513  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
1514  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
1515  DCHECK_EQ(element_size_log2, 0);
1516  if (index.valid()) {
1517  DCHECK_EQ(displacement, 0);
1518  inputs[input_count++] =
1519  g.GetEffectiveIndexOperand(index.value(), &addressing_mode);
1520  } else if (displacement != 0) {
1521  DCHECK(ValueFitsIntoImmediate(displacement));
1522  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(displacement);
1523  addressing_mode = kMode_MRI;
1524  } else {
1525  addressing_mode = kMode_MR;
1526  }
1527  opcode = GetSeqCstStoreOpcode(store_rep);
1528  } else {
1529  if (ElementSizeLog2Of(store_rep.representation()) <
1530  kSystemPointerSizeLog2) {
1531  if (V<Word64> value64;
1532  selector->MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(value, &value64)) {
1533  value = value64;
1534  }
1535  }
1536 
1537  addressing_mode = g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
1538  store, inputs, &input_count, reg_kind);
1539  InstructionOperand value_operand = g.CanBeImmediate(value)
1540  ? g.UseImmediate(value)
1541  : g.UseRegister(value, reg_kind);
1542  inputs[input_count++] = value_operand;
1543  opcode = GetStoreOpcode(store.ts_stored_rep());
1544  }
1545 
1546  InstructionCode code = opcode
1547  | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode)
1548  | AccessModeField::encode(access_mode);
1549  selector->Emit(code, 0, static_cast<InstructionOperand*>(nullptr),
1550  input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
1551  }
1552 }
1553 
1554 } // namespace

1572 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1573 void InstructionSelector::VisitStoreLane(OpIndex node) {
1574  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1575  const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& store = Get(node).Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>();
1576  InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
1577  switch (store.lane_kind) {
1578  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8:
1579  opcode = kX64Pextrb;
1580  break;
1581  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16:
1582  opcode = kX64Pextrw;
1583  break;
1584  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32:
1585  opcode = kX64S128Store32Lane;
1586  break;
1587  case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64:
1588  opcode = kX64S128Store64Lane;
1589  break;
1590  }
1591 
1592  InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1593  size_t input_count = 0;
1594  AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1595  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
1596  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1597 
1598  if (store.kind.with_trap_handler) {
1599  opcode |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
1600  }
1601 
1602  InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(store.value());
1603  inputs[input_count++] = value_operand;
1604  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(store.lane);
1605  DCHECK_GE(4, input_count);
1606  Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
1607 }

1609 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

1611 // Shared routine for multiple binary operations.
1612 static void VisitBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1613  InstructionCode opcode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1614  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1615  const Operation& binop = selector->Get(node);
1616  DCHECK_EQ(binop.input_count, 2);
1617  auto left = binop.input(0);
1618  auto right = binop.input(1);
1619  if (selector->IsCommutative(node)) {
1620  if (selector->Is<ConstantOp>(left) && !selector->Is<ConstantOp>(right)) {
1621  std::swap(left, right);
1622  }
1623  }
1624  InstructionOperand inputs[8];
1625  size_t input_count = 0;
1626  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
1627  size_t output_count = 0;
1628 
1629  // TODO(turbofan): match complex addressing modes.
1630  if (left == right) {
1631  // If both inputs refer to the same operand, enforce allocating a register
1632  // for both of them to ensure that we don't end up generating code like
1633  // this:
1634  //
1635  // mov rax, [rbp-0x10]
1636  // add rax, [rbp-0x10]
1637  // jo label
1638  InstructionOperand const input = g.UseRegister(left);
1639  inputs[input_count++] = input;
1640  inputs[input_count++] = input;
1641  } else if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
1642  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left);
1643  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(right);
1644  } else {
1645  int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
1646  if (selector->IsCommutative(node) && g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right) &&
1647  (!g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(left) ||
1648  !g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, right, effect_level))) {
1649  std::swap(left, right);
1650  }
1651  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, right, effect_level)) {
1652  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left);
1653  AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1654  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(right, inputs, &input_count);
1655  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1656  } else {
1657  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left);
1658  inputs[input_count++] = g.Use(right);
1659  }
1660  }
1661 
1662  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
1663 
1664  DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
1665  DCHECK_EQ(1u, output_count);
1666  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
1667  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
1668 
1669  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
1670  inputs, cont);
1671 }
1672 
1673 // Shared routine for multiple binary operations.
1674 std::optional<int32_t> GetWord32Constant(
1675  InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1676  bool allow_implicit_int64_truncation = true) {
1677  if (const auto* constant = selector->TryCast<ConstantOp>(node)) {
1678  if (constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32) {
1679  return constant->word32();
1680  }
1681  if (allow_implicit_int64_truncation &&
1682  constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64) {
1683  return static_cast<int32_t>(constant->word64());
1684  }
1685  }
1686  return std::nullopt;
1687 }
1688 
1689 static void VisitBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1690  InstructionCode opcode) {
1691  FlagsContinuation cont;
1692  VisitBinop(selector, node, opcode, &cont);
1693 }
1694 
1695 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32And(OpIndex node) {
1696  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1697  V<Word32> left;
1698  if (MatchWordBinop<Word32>(node, &left, 0xFF)) {
1699  if (this->is_load(left)) {
1700  LoadRepresentation load_rep = load_view(left).loaded_rep();
1701  if (load_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8 &&
1702  load_rep.IsUnsigned()) {
1703  EmitIdentity(node);
1704  return;
1705  }
1706  }
1707  Emit(kX64Movzxbl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left));
1708  return;
1709  } else if (MatchWordBinop<Word32>(node, &left, 0xFFFF)) {
1710  if (this->is_load(left)) {
1711  LoadRepresentation load_rep = load_view(left).loaded_rep();
1712  if ((load_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord16 ||
1713  load_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) &&
1714  load_rep.IsUnsigned()) {
1715  EmitIdentity(node);
1716  return;
1717  }
1718  }
1719  Emit(kX64Movzxwl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left));
1720  return;
1721  }
1722  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64And32);
1723 }
1724 
1725 std::optional<uint64_t> TryGetRightWordConstant(InstructionSelector* selector,
1726  OpIndex node) {
1727  if (const WordBinopOp* binop = selector->Get(node).TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
1728  uint64_t value;
1729  if (selector->MatchUnsignedIntegralConstant(binop->right(), &value)) {
1730  return value;
1731  }
1732  }
1733  return std::nullopt;
1734 }
1735 
1736 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64And(OpIndex node) {
1737  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1738  if (std::optional<uint64_t> constant = TryGetRightWordConstant(this, node)) {
1739  OpIndex left = Get(node).input(0);
1740  if (*constant == 0xFF) {
1741  Emit(kX64Movzxbq, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left));
1742  return;
1743  } else if (*constant == 0xFFFF) {
1744  Emit(kX64Movzxwq, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left));
1745  return;
1746  } else if (*constant == 0xFFFFFFFF) {
1747  Emit(kX64Movl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left));
1748  return;
1749  } else if (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::min() <= *constant &&
1750  *constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
1751  Emit(kX64And32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1752  g.UseImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(*constant)));
1753  return;
1754  }
1755  }
1756  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64And);
1757 }
1758 
1759 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Or(OpIndex node) {
1760  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Or32);
1761 }
1762 
1763 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Or(OpIndex node) {
1764  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Or);
1765 }

1767 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Xor(OpIndex node) {
1768  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1769  if (std::optional<uint64_t> constant = TryGetRightWordConstant(this, node)) {
1770  if (*constant == static_cast<uint64_t>(-1)) {
1771  Emit(kX64Not32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1772  g.UseRegister(Get(node).input(0)));
1773  return;
1774  }
1775  }
1776  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Xor32);
1777 }
1778 
1779 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Xor(OpIndex node) {
1780  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1781  if (std::optional<uint64_t> constant = TryGetRightWordConstant(this, node)) {
1782  if (*constant == static_cast<uint64_t>(-1)) {
1783  Emit(kX64Not, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1784  g.UseRegister(Get(node).input(0)));
1785  return;
1786  }
1787  }
1788  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Xor);
1789 }

1791 void InstructionSelector::VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(
1792  OpIndex node, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1793  const StackPointerGreaterThanOp& op = Cast<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>(node);
1794  InstructionCode opcode =
1795  kArchStackPointerGreaterThan |
1796  StackCheckField::encode(static_cast<StackCheckKind>(op.kind));
1797 
1798  int effect_level = GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
1799 
1800  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1801  OpIndex value = op.stack_limit();
1802  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(kX64Cmp, node, value, effect_level)) {
1803  DCHECK(this->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(value));
1804 
1805  // GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand can create at most 3 inputs.
1806  static constexpr int kMaxInputCount = 3;
1807 
1808  size_t input_count = 0;
1809  InstructionOperand inputs[kMaxInputCount];
1810  AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1811  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(value, inputs, &input_count);
1812  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1813  DCHECK_LE(input_count, kMaxInputCount);
1814 
1815  EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, cont);
1816  } else {
1817  EmitWithContinuation(opcode, g.UseRegister(value), cont);
1818  }
1819 }

1823 // Shared routine for multiple 32-bit shift operations.
1824 // TODO(bmeurer): Merge this with VisitWord64Shift using template magic?
1825 void VisitWord32Shift(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1826  ArchOpcode opcode) {
1827  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1828  const ShiftOp& op = selector->Cast<ShiftOp>(node);
1829  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
1830  auto left = op.left();
1831  auto right = op.right();
1832 
1833  if (V<Word64> left64; selector->MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(left, &left64)) {
1834  left = left64;
1835  }
1836 
1837  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
1838  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1839  g.UseImmediate(right));
1840  } else {
1841  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1842  g.UseFixed(right, rcx));
1843  }
1844 }
1845 
1846 // Shared routine for multiple 64-bit shift operations.
1847 // TODO(bmeurer): Merge this with VisitWord32Shift using template magic?
1848 void VisitWord64Shift(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
1849  ArchOpcode opcode) {
1850  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1851  const ShiftOp& op = selector->Cast<ShiftOp>(node);
1852  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
1853  auto left = op.left();
1854  auto right = op.right();
1855 
1856  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
1857  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Implement this for Turboshaft.
1858 #if 0
1859  Int64BinopMatcher m(node);
1860  if (opcode == kX64Shr && m.left().IsChangeUint32ToUint64() &&
1861  m.right().HasResolvedValue() && m.right().ResolvedValue() < 32 &&
1862  m.right().ResolvedValue() >= 0) {
1863  opcode = kX64Shr32;
1864  left = left->InputAt(0);
1865  }
1866 #endif
1867  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1868  g.UseImmediate(right));
1869  } else {
1870  // TODO(nicohartmann@): Implement this for Turboshaft.
1871 #if 0
1872  Int64BinopMatcher m(node);
1873  if (m.right().IsWord64And()) {
1874  Int64BinopMatcher mright(right);
1875  if (mright.right().Is(0x3F)) {
1876  right = mright.left().node();
1877  }
1878  }
1879 #endif
1880  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1881  g.UseFixed(right, rcx));
1882  }
1883 }
1884 
1885 // Shared routine for multiple shift operations with continuation.
1886 bool TryVisitWordShift(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, int bits,
1887  ArchOpcode opcode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1888  DCHECK(bits == 32 || bits == 64);
1889  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1890  const ShiftOp& op = selector->Cast<ShiftOp>(node);
1891  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
1892  auto left = op.left();
1893  auto right = op.right();
1894 
1895  // If the shift count is 0, the flags are not affected.
1896  if (!g.CanBeImmediate(right) ||
1897  (g.GetImmediateIntegerValue(right) & (bits - 1)) == 0) {
1898  return false;
1899  }
1900  InstructionOperand output = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
1901  InstructionOperand inputs[2];
1902  inputs[0] = g.UseRegister(left);
1903  inputs[1] = g.UseImmediate(right);
1904  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 1, &output, 2, inputs, cont);
1905  return true;
1906 }
1907 
1908 void EmitLea(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
1909  OpIndex result, OpIndex index, int scale, OpIndex base,
1910  int64_t displacement, DisplacementMode displacement_mode) {
1911  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
1912 
1913  InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1914  size_t input_count = 0;
1915  AddressingMode mode =
1916  g.GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(index, scale, base, displacement,
1917  displacement_mode, inputs, &input_count);
1918 
1919  DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
1920  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
1921 
1922  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
1923  outputs[0] = g.DefineAsRegister(result);
1924 
1925  opcode = AddressingModeField::encode(mode) | opcode;
1926 
1927  selector->Emit(opcode, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs);
1928 }

1932 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Shl(OpIndex node) {
1933  bool plus_one;
1934  OpIndex index;
1935  int scale;
1936  if (MatchScaledIndex(this, node, &index, &scale, &plus_one)) {
1937  OpIndex base = plus_one ? index : OpIndex{};
1938  EmitLea(this, kX64Lea32, node, index, scale, base, 0,
1939  kPositiveDisplacement);
1940  return;
1941  }
1942  VisitWord32Shift(this, node, kX64Shl32);
1943 }
1944 
1945 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Shl(OpIndex node) {
1946  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
1947  // TODO(nicohartmann,dmercadier): Port the Int64ScaleMatcher part of the
1948  // Turbofan version. This is used in the builtin pipeline.
1949  const ShiftOp& shift = this->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
1950  OpIndex left = shift.left();
1951  OpIndex right = shift.right();
1952  int32_t cst;
1953  if ((this->Get(left).template Is<Opmask::kChangeUint32ToUint64>() ||
1954  this->Get(left).template Is<Opmask::kChangeInt32ToInt64>()) &&
1955  this->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(right, &cst) &&
1956  base::IsInRange(cst, 32, 63)) {
1957  // There's no need to sign/zero-extend to 64-bit if we shift out the
1958  // upper 32 bits anyway.
1959  Emit(kX64Shl, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
1960  g.UseRegister(this->Get(left).input(0)), g.UseImmediate(right));
1961  return;
1962  }
1963  VisitWord64Shift(this, node, kX64Shl);
1964 }

1966 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Shr(OpIndex node) {
1967  VisitWord32Shift(this, node, kX64Shr32);
1968 }

1972 inline AddressingMode AddDisplacementToAddressingMode(AddressingMode mode) {
1973  switch (mode) {
1974  case kMode_MR:
1975  return kMode_MRI;
1976  case kMode_MR1:
1977  return kMode_MR1I;
1978  case kMode_MR2:
1979  return kMode_MR2I;
1980  case kMode_MR4:
1981  return kMode_MR4I;
1982  case kMode_MR8:
1983  return kMode_MR8I;
1984  case kMode_M1:
1985  return kMode_M1I;
1986  case kMode_M2:
1987  return kMode_M2I;
1988  case kMode_M4:
1989  return kMode_M4I;
1990  case kMode_M8:
1991  return kMode_M8I;
1992  case kMode_None:
1993  case kMode_MRI:
1994  case kMode_MR1I:
1995  case kMode_MR2I:
1996  case kMode_MR4I:
1997  case kMode_MR8I:
1998  case kMode_M1I:
1999  case kMode_M2I:
2000  case kMode_M4I:
2001  case kMode_M8I:
2002  case kMode_Root:
2003  case kMode_MCR:
2004  case kMode_MCRI:
2005  UNREACHABLE();
2006  }
2007  UNREACHABLE();
2008 }
2009 
2010 // {node} should be a right shift. If its input is a 64-bit Load and {node}
2011 // shifts it to the right by 32 bits, then this function emits a 32-bit Load of
2012 // the high bits only (allowing 1. to load fewer bits and 2. to get rid of the
2013 // shift).
2014 bool TryEmitLoadForLoadWord64AndShiftRight(InstructionSelector* selector,
2015  OpIndex node,
2016  InstructionCode opcode) {
2017  DCHECK(selector->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>().IsRightShift());
2018  const ShiftOp& shift = selector->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
2019  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2020  if (selector->CanCover(node, shift.left()) &&
2021  selector->Get(shift.left()).Is<LoadOp>() &&
2022  selector->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(shift.right(), 32)) {
2023  DCHECK_EQ(selector->GetEffectLevel(node),
2024  selector->GetEffectLevel(shift.left()));
2025  // Just load and sign-extend the interesting 4 bytes instead. This happens,
2026  // for example, when we're loading and untagging SMIs.
2027  auto m =
2028  TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(selector, shift.left());
2029  if (m.has_value() &&
2030  (m->displacement == 0 || ValueFitsIntoImmediate(m->displacement))) {
2031 #ifdef V8_IS_TSAN
2032  // On TSAN builds we require one scratch register. Because of this we also
2033  // have to modify the inputs to take into account possible aliasing and
2034  // use UseUniqueRegister which is not required for non-TSAN builds.
2035  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
2036  size_t temp_count = arraysize(temps);
2037  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister;
2038 #else
2039  InstructionOperand* temps = nullptr;
2040  size_t temp_count = 0;
2041  auto reg_kind = OperandGenerator::RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister;
2042 #endif // V8_IS_TSAN
2043  size_t input_count = 0;
2044  InstructionOperand inputs[3];
2045  AddressingMode mode = g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
2046  shift.left(), inputs, &input_count, reg_kind);
2047  if (m->displacement == 0) {
2048  // Make sure that the addressing mode indicates the presence of an
2049  // immediate displacement. It seems that we never use M1 and M2, but we
2050  // handle them here anyways.
2051  mode = AddDisplacementToAddressingMode(mode);
2052  inputs[input_count++] =
2053  ImmediateOperand(ImmediateOperand::INLINE_INT32, 4);
2054  } else {
2055  // In the case that the base address was zero, the displacement will be
2056  // in a register and replacing it with an immediate is not allowed. This
2057  // usually only happens in dead code anyway.
2058  if (!inputs[input_count - 1].IsImmediate()) return false;
2059  inputs[input_count - 1] =
2060  ImmediateOperand(ImmediateOperand::INLINE_INT32,
2061  static_cast<int32_t>(m->displacement) + 4);
2062  }
2063  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
2064  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
2065  selector->Emit(code, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
2066  return true;
2067  }
2068  }
2069  return false;
2070 }
2071 
2072 } // namespace

2076  VisitWord64Shift(this, node, kX64Shr);
2077 }

2145 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Add(OpIndex node) {
2146  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2147 
2148  std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch> m;
2149  const WordBinopOp& add = Cast<WordBinopOp>(node);
2150  OpIndex left = add.left();
2151  OpIndex right = add.right();
2152  // No need to truncate the values before Int32Add.
2153  if (V<Word64> left64; MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(left, &left64)) {
2154  left = left64;
2155  }
2156  if (V<Word64> right64; MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(right, &right64)) {
2157  right = right64;
2158  }
2159 
2160  DCHECK(LhsIsNotOnlyConstant(this->turboshaft_graph(), left, right));
2161 
2162  // Try to match the Add to a leal pattern
2163  m = TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64ForWordBinop(this, left,
2164  right, true);
2165 
2166  if (m.has_value()) {
2167  if (ValueFitsIntoImmediate(m->displacement)) {
2168  EmitLea(this, kX64Lea32, node, m->index, m->scale, m->base,
2169  m->displacement, m->displacement_mode);
2170  return;
2171  }
2172  }
2173 
2174  // No leal pattern match, use addl
2175  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add32);
2176 }
2177 
2178 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt64Add(OpIndex node) {
2179  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2180  // Try to match the Add to a leaq pattern
2181  if (auto match = TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(this, node)) {
2182  if (ValueFitsIntoImmediate(match->displacement)) {
2183  EmitLea(this, kX64Lea, node, match->index, match->scale, match->base,
2184  match->displacement, match->displacement_mode);
2185  return;
2186  }
2187  }
2188 
2189  // No leal pattern match, use addq
2190  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add);
2191 }

2197  return VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add, &cont);

2200  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add, &cont);

2203 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Sub(OpIndex node) {
2204  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2205  auto [left, right] = Inputs<WordBinopOp>(node);
2206  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
2207  int32_t imm = g.GetImmediateIntegerValue(right);
2208  if (imm == 0) {
2209  if (this->Get(left).outputs_rep()[0] ==
2210  RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
2211  // {EmitIdentity} reuses the virtual register of the first input
2212  // for the output. This is exactly what we want here.
2213  EmitIdentity(node);
2214  } else {
2215  // Emit "movl" for subtraction of 0.
2216  Emit(kX64Movl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left));
2217  }
2218  } else {
2219  // Omit truncation and turn subtractions of constant values into immediate
2220  // "leal" instructions by negating the value.
2221  Emit(kX64Lea32 | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI),
2222  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left),
2223  g.TempImmediate(base::NegateWithWraparound(imm)));
2224  }
2225  return;
2226  }
2227 
2228  if (MatchIntegralZero(left)) {
2229  Emit(kX64Neg32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(right));
2230  return;
2231  }
2232 
2233  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Sub32);
2234 }
2235 
2236 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt64Sub(OpIndex node) {
2237  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2238  const WordBinopOp& binop = this->Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2239  DCHECK_EQ(binop.kind, WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub);
2240 
2241  if (MatchIntegralZero(binop.left())) {
2242  Emit(kX64Neg, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(binop.right()));
2243  return;
2244  }
2245  if (auto constant = TryGetRightWordConstant(this, node)) {
2246  int64_t immediate_value = -*constant;
2247  if (ValueFitsIntoImmediate(immediate_value)) {
2248  // Turn subtractions of constant values into immediate "leaq" instructions
2249  // by negating the value.
2250  Emit(kX64Lea | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI),
2251  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(binop.left()),
2252  g.TempImmediate(static_cast<int32_t>(immediate_value)));
2253  return;
2254  }
2255  }
2256  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Sub);
2257 }
2258 
2259 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt64SubWithOverflow(OpIndex node) {
2260  OptionalOpIndex ovf = FindProjection(node, 1);
2261  if (ovf.valid()) {
2262  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kOverflow, ovf.value());
2263  return VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Sub, &cont);
2264  }
2265  FlagsContinuation cont;
2266  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Sub, &cont);
2267 }

2271 void VisitMul(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, ArchOpcode opcode) {
2272  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2273  auto [left, right] = selector->Inputs<WordBinopOp>(node);
2274  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
2275  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(left),
2276  g.UseImmediate(right));
2277  } else {
2278  if (g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right)) {
2279  std::swap(left, right);
2280  }
2281  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(left),
2282  g.Use(right));
2283  }
2284 }
2285 
2286 void VisitMulHigh(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
2287  ArchOpcode opcode) {
2288  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2289  auto [left, right] = selector->Inputs<WordBinopOp>(node);
2290  if (selector->IsLive(left) && !selector->IsLive(right)) {
2291  std::swap(left, right);
2292  }
2293  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(rax)};
2294  // TODO(turbofan): We use UseUniqueRegister here to improve register
2295  // allocation.
2296  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsFixed(node, rdx), g.UseFixed(left, rax),
2297  g.UseUniqueRegister(right), arraysize(temps), temps);
2298 }

2300 void VisitDiv(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, ArchOpcode opcode) {

2302  auto [left, right] = selector->Inputs<WordBinopOp>(node);
2303  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(rdx)};
2304  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsFixed(node, rax), g.UseFixed(left, rax),
2305  g.UseUniqueRegister(right), arraysize(temps), temps);
2306 }

2308 void VisitMod(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, ArchOpcode opcode) {
2309  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2310  auto [left, right] = selector->Inputs<WordBinopOp>(node);
2311  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(rax)};
2312  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsFixed(node, rdx), g.UseFixed(left, rax),
2313  g.UseUniqueRegister(right), arraysize(temps), temps);
2314 }
2315 
2316 } // namespace

2318 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Mul(OpIndex node) {
2319  if (auto m = TryMatchScaledIndex32(this, node, true)) {
2320  EmitLea(this, kX64Lea32, node, m->index, m->scale, m->base, 0,
2321  kPositiveDisplacement);
2322  return;
2323  }
2324  VisitMul(this, node, kX64Imul32);
2325 }

2328  OptionalOpIndex ovf = FindProjection(node, 1);
2329  if (ovf.valid()) {
2330  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kOverflow, ovf.value());
2331  return VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Imul32, &cont);
2332  }
2333  FlagsContinuation cont;
2334  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Imul32, &cont);
2335 }
