2404 // TryTruncateFloat32ToInt64 and TryTruncateFloat64ToInt64 operations attempt
2405 // truncation from 32|64-bit float to 64-bit integer by performing roughly the
2406 // following steps:
2407 // 1. Round the original FP value to zero, store in `rounded`;
2408 // 2. Convert the original FP value to integer;
2409 // 3. Convert the integer value back to floating point, store in
2410 // `converted_back`;
2411 // 4. If `rounded` == `converted_back`:
2412 // Set Projection(1) := 1; -- the value was in range
2413 // Else:
2414 // Set Projection(1) := 0; -- the value was out of range
2415 void InstructionSelector::VisitTryTruncateFloat32ToInt64(OpIndex node) {
2416  const TryChangeOp& op = Cast<TryChangeOp>(node);
2417  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
2418  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2419  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(op.input())};
2420  InstructionOperand outputs[2];
2421  InstructionOperand temps[1];
2422  size_t output_count = 0;
2423  size_t temp_count = 0;
2424  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2425 
2426  OptionalOpIndex success_output = FindProjection(node, 1);
2427  if (success_output.valid()) {
2428  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(success_output.value());
2429  temps[temp_count++] = g.TempSimd128Register();
2430  }
2431 
2432  Emit(kSSEFloat32ToInt64, output_count, outputs, 1, inputs, temp_count, temps);
2433 }
2434 
2435 // TryTruncateFloatNNToUintDD operations attempt truncation from NN-bit
2436 // float to DD-bit integer by using ConvertFloatToUintDD macro instructions.
2437 // It performs a float-to-int instruction, rounding to zero and tests whether
2438 // the result is positive integer (the default, fast case), which means the
2439 // value is in range. Then, we set Projection(1) := 1. Else, we perform
2440 // additional subtraction, conversion and (in case the value was originally
2441 // negative, but still within range) we restore it and set Projection(1) := 1.
2442 // In all other cases we set Projection(1) := 0, denoting value out of range.
2443 void InstructionSelector::VisitTryTruncateFloat64ToUint32(OpIndex node) {
2444  const TryChangeOp& op = Cast<TryChangeOp>(node);
2445  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
2446  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2447  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(op.input())};
2448  InstructionOperand outputs[2];
2449  size_t output_count = 0;
2450  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
2451 
2452  OptionalOpIndex success_output = FindProjection(node, 1);
2453  if (success_output.valid()) {
2454  outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(success_output.value());
2455  }
2456 
2457  Emit(kSSEFloat64ToUint32, output_count, outputs, 1, inputs);
2458 }
2459

2539 
2540 void InstructionSelector::VisitChangeInt32ToInt64(OpIndex node) {
2541  const ChangeOp& op = Cast<ChangeOp>(node);
2542  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
2543 
2544  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2545  auto value = op.input();
2546  if (this->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(value) && CanCover(node, value)) {
2547  LoadRepresentation load_rep = load_view(value).loaded_rep();
2548  MachineRepresentation rep = load_rep.representation();
2549  InstructionCode opcode;
2550  switch (rep) {
2551  case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
2552  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
2553  opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kX64Movsxbq : kX64Movzxbq;
2554  break;
2555  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
2556  opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kX64Movsxwq : kX64Movzxwq;
2557  break;
2558  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
2559  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
2560  // Since BitcastElider may remove nodes of
2561  // IrOpcode::kTruncateInt64ToInt32 and directly use the inputs, values
2562  // with kWord64 can also reach this line.
2563  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
2564  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
2565  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
2566  // ChangeInt32ToInt64 must interpret its input as a _signed_ 32-bit
2567  // integer, so here we must sign-extend the loaded value in any case.
2568  opcode = kX64Movsxlq;
2569  break;
2570  default:
2571  UNREACHABLE();
2572  }
2573  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
2574  size_t input_count = 0;
2575  InstructionOperand inputs[3];
2576  AddressingMode mode =
2577  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(value, inputs, &input_count);
2578  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
2579  Emit(opcode, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs);
2580  } else {
2581  Emit(kX64Movsxlq, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(value));
2582  }
2583 }
2584 
2585 bool InstructionSelector::ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64NoPhis(OpIndex node) {
2586  const Operation& op = Get(node);
2587  switch (op.opcode) {
2588  case Opcode::kWordBinop: {
2589  const auto& binop = op.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2590  if (binop.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
2591  DCHECK(binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd ||
2592  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr ||
2593  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor ||
2594  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd ||
2595  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub ||
2596  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kMul ||
2597  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedDiv ||
2598  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedDiv ||
2599  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMod ||
2600  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedMod ||
2601  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMulOverflownBits ||
2602  binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedMulOverflownBits);
2603  return true;
2604  }
2605  case Opcode::kShift: {
2606  const auto& shift = op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
2607  if (shift.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
2608  DCHECK(shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft ||
2609  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical ||
2610  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic ||
2611  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros ||
2612  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateLeft ||
2613  shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateRight);
2614  return true;
2615  }
2616  case Opcode::kComparison: {
2617  const auto& comparison = op.Cast<ComparisonOp>();
2618  DCHECK(comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual ||
2619  comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan ||
2620  comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual ||
2621  comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan ||
2622  comparison.kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
2623  return comparison.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2624  }
2625  case Opcode::kProjection: {
2626  const auto& projection = op.Cast<ProjectionOp>();
2627  if (const auto* binop =
2628  this->Get(projection.input()).TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>()) {
2629  DCHECK(binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd ||
2630  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub ||
2631  binop->kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul);
2632  return binop->rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
2633  }
2634  return false;
2635  }
2636  case Opcode::kLoad: {
2637  const auto& load = op.Cast<LoadOp>();
2638  // The movzxbl/movsxbl/movzxwl/movsxwl/movl operations implicitly
2639  // zero-extend to 64-bit on x64, so the zero-extension is a no-op.
2640  switch (load.loaded_rep.ToMachineType().representation()) {
2641  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
2642  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
2643  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
2644  return true;
2645  default:
2646  break;
2647  }
2648  return false;
2649  }
2650  case Opcode::kConstant: {
2651  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2652  // Constants are loaded with movl or movq, or xorl for zero; see
2653  // CodeGenerator::AssembleMove. So any non-negative constant that fits
2654  // in a 32-bit signed integer is zero-extended to 64 bits.
2655  if (g.CanBeImmediate(node)) {
2656  return g.GetImmediateIntegerValue(node) >= 0;
2657  }
2658  return false;
2659  }
2660  case Opcode::kChange:
2661  return Is<Opmask::kTruncateWord64ToWord32>(node);
2662  default:
2663  return false;
2664  }
2665 }
2666 
2667 void InstructionSelector::VisitChangeUint32ToUint64(OpIndex node) {
2668  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2669  const ChangeOp& op = Cast<ChangeOp>(node);
2670  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
2671  OpIndex value = op.input();
2672  if (ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64(value)) {
2673  // These 32-bit operations implicitly zero-extend to 64-bit on x64, so the
2674  // zero-extension is a no-op.
2675  return EmitIdentity(node);
2676  }
2677  Emit(kX64Movl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(value));
2678 }

2698 void VisitRRO(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
2699  InstructionCode opcode) {
2700  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2701  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
2702  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
2703  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)),
2704  g.Use(op.input(1)));
2705 }
2706 
2707 void VisitFloatBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
2708  InstructionCode avx_opcode, InstructionCode sse_opcode) {
2709  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2710  const FloatBinopOp& op = selector->Cast<FloatBinopOp>(node);
2711  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
2712  auto left = op.left();
2713  auto right = op.right();
2714  InstructionOperand inputs[8];
2715  size_t input_count = 0;
2716  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
2717  size_t output_count = 0;
2718  OpIndex trapping_load = {};
2719 
2720  if (left == right) {
2721  // If both inputs refer to the same operand, enforce allocating a register
2722  // for both of them to ensure that we don't end up generating code like
2723  // this:
2724  //
2725  // movss rax, [rbp-0x10]
2726  // addss rax, [rbp-0x10]
2727  // jo label
2728  InstructionOperand const input = g.UseRegister(left);
2729  inputs[input_count++] = input;
2730  inputs[input_count++] = input;
2731  } else {
2732  int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node);
2733  if (selector->IsCommutative(node) &&
2734  (g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right) ||
2735  g.CanBeMemoryOperand(avx_opcode, node, left, effect_level)) &&
2736  (!g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(left) ||
2737  !g.CanBeMemoryOperand(avx_opcode, node, right, effect_level))) {
2738  std::swap(left, right);
2739  }
2740  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(avx_opcode, node, right, effect_level)) {
2741  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left);
2742  AddressingMode addressing_mode =
2743  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(right, inputs, &input_count);
2744  avx_opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
2745  sse_opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
2746  if (selector->IsProtectedLoad(right) &&
2747  selector->CanCoverProtectedLoad(node, right)) {
2748  // In {CanBeMemoryOperand} we have already checked that
2749  // CanCover(node, right) succeeds, which means that there is no
2750  // instruction with Effects required_when_unused or
2751  // produces.control_flow between right and node, and that the node has
2752  // no other uses. Therefore, we can record the fact that 'right' was
2753  // embedded in 'node' and we can later delete the Load instruction.
2754  selector->MarkAsProtected(node);
2755  avx_opcode |=
2756  AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
2757  sse_opcode |=
2758  AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
2759  selector->SetProtectedLoadToRemove(right);
2760  trapping_load = right;
2761  }
2762  } else {
2763  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(left);
2764  inputs[input_count++] = g.Use(right);
2765  }
2766  }
2767 
2768  DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
2769  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
2770  InstructionCode code = selector->IsSupported(AVX) ? avx_opcode : sse_opcode;
2771  outputs[output_count++] = selector->IsSupported(AVX)
2772  ? g.DefineAsRegister(node)
2773  : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
2774  DCHECK_EQ(1u, output_count);
2775  DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
2776  Instruction* instr =
2777  selector->Emit(code, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs);
2778  if (trapping_load.valid()) {
2779  selector->UpdateSourcePosition(instr, trapping_load);
2780  }
2781 }
2782 
2783 void VisitFloatUnop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node, OpIndex input,
2784  InstructionCode opcode) {
2785  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
2786  if (selector->IsSupported(AVX)) {
2787  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input));
2788  } else {
2789  selector->Emit(opcode, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(input));
2790  }
2791 }

2903 void InstructionSelector::VisitTruncateInt64ToInt32(OpIndex node) {
2904  // We rely on the fact that TruncateInt64ToInt32 zero extends the
2905  // value (see ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64). So all code paths here
2906  // have to satisfy that condition.
2907  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
2908  const ChangeOp& op = Cast<ChangeOp>(node);
2909  OpIndex value = op.input();
2910  bool can_cover = false;
2911  if (const TaggedBitcastOp* value_op =
2912  TryCast<Opmask::kBitcastTaggedToWordPtrForTagAndSmiBits>(value)) {
2913  can_cover = CanCover(node, value) && CanCover(node, value_op->input());
2914  value = value_op->input();
2915  } else {
2916  can_cover = CanCover(node, value);
2917  }
2918  if (can_cover) {
2919  const Operation& value_op = Get(value);
2920  if (const ShiftOp * shift;
2921  (shift = value_op.TryCast<Opmask::kWord64ShiftRightArithmetic>()) ||
2922  (shift = value_op.TryCast<Opmask::kWord64ShiftRightLogical>())) {
2923  if (this->MatchIntegralWord32Constant(shift->right(), 32)) {
2924  if (CanCover(value, shift->left()) &&
2925  TryEmitLoadForLoadWord64AndShiftRight(this, value, kX64Movl)) {
2926  // We just defined and emitted a 32-bit Load for {value} (the upper
2927  // 32 bits only since it was getting shifted by 32 bits to the right
2928  // afterwards); we now define {node} as a rename of {value} without
2929  // needing to do a truncation.
2930  return EmitIdentity(node);
2931  }
2932  Emit(kX64Shr, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(shift->left()),
2933  g.TempImmediate(32));
2934  return;
2935  }
2936  }
2937  }
2938  Emit(kX64Movl, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(value));
2939 }

3050 void InstructionSelector::EmitPrepareArguments(
3051  ZoneVector<PushParameter>* arguments, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3052  OpIndex node) {
3053  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
3054 
3055  // Prepare for C function call.
3056  if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3057  Emit(kArchPrepareCallCFunction | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(
3058  call_descriptor->ParameterCount())),
3059  0, nullptr, 0, nullptr);
3060 
3061  // Poke any stack arguments.
3062  for (size_t n = 0; n < arguments->size(); ++n) {
3063  PushParameter input = (*arguments)[n];
3064  if (input.node.valid()) {
3065  int slot = static_cast<int>(n);
3066  InstructionOperand value = g.CanBeImmediate(input.node)
3067  ? g.UseImmediate(input.node)
3068  : g.UseRegister(input.node);
3069  Emit(kX64Poke | MiscField::encode(slot), g.NoOutput(), value);
3070  }
3071  }
3072  } else {
3073  // Push any stack arguments.
3074  int effect_level = GetEffectLevel(node);
3075  int stack_decrement = 0;
3076  for (PushParameter input : base::Reversed(*arguments)) {
3077  stack_decrement += kSystemPointerSize;
3078  // Skip holes in the param array. These represent both extra slots for
3079  // multi-slot values and padding slots for alignment.
3080  if (!input.node.valid()) continue;
3081  InstructionOperand decrement = g.UseImmediate(stack_decrement);
3082  stack_decrement = 0;
3083  if (g.CanBeImmediate(input.node)) {
3084  Emit(kX64Push, g.NoOutput(), decrement, g.UseImmediate(input.node));
3085  } else if (IsSupported(INTEL_ATOM) ||
3086  sequence()->IsFP(GetVirtualRegister(input.node))) {
3087  // TODO(titzer): X64Push cannot handle stack->stack double moves
3088  // because there is no way to encode fixed double slots.
3089  Emit(kX64Push, g.NoOutput(), decrement, g.UseRegister(input.node));
3090  } else if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(kX64Push, node, input.node,
3091  effect_level)) {
3092  InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3093  InstructionOperand inputs[5];
3094  size_t input_count = 0;
3095  inputs[input_count++] = decrement;
3096  AddressingMode mode = g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
3097  input.node, inputs, &input_count);
3098  InstructionCode opcode = kX64Push | AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
3099  Emit(opcode, 0, outputs, input_count, inputs);
3100  } else {
3101  Emit(kX64Push, g.NoOutput(), decrement, g.UseAny(input.node));
3102  }
3103  }
3104  }
3105 }
3106 
3107 void InstructionSelector::EmitPrepareResults(
3108  ZoneVector<PushParameter>* results, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3109  OpIndex node) {
3110  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
3111  for (PushParameter output : *results) {
3112  if (!output.location.IsCallerFrameSlot()) continue;
3113  // Skip any alignment holes in nodes.
3114  if (output.node.valid()) {
3115  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall());
3116  if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float32()) {
3117  MarkAsFloat32(output.node);
3118  } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float64()) {
3119  MarkAsFloat64(output.node);
3120  } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Simd128()) {
3121  MarkAsSimd128(output.node);
3122  }
3123  InstructionOperand result = g.DefineAsRegister(output.node);
3124  int offset = call_descriptor->GetOffsetToReturns();
3125  int reverse_slot = -output.location.GetLocation() - offset;
3126  InstructionOperand slot = g.UseImmediate(reverse_slot);
3127  Emit(kX64Peek, 1, &result, 1, &slot);
3128  }
3129  }
3130 }

3136 void VisitCompareWithMemoryOperand(InstructionSelector* selector,
3137  InstructionCode opcode, OpIndex left,
3138  InstructionOperand right,
3139  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3140  DCHECK(selector->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(left));
3141  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3142  size_t input_count = 0;
3143  InstructionOperand inputs[6];
3144  AddressingMode addressing_mode =
3145  g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(left, inputs, &input_count);
3146  opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
3147  inputs[input_count++] = right;
3148  if (cont->IsSelect()) {
3149  if (opcode == kUnorderedEqual) {
3150  cont->Negate();
3151  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(cont->true_value());
3152  inputs[input_count++] = g.Use(cont->false_value());
3153  } else {
3154  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(cont->false_value());
3155  inputs[input_count++] = g.Use(cont->true_value());
3156  }
3157  }
3158 
3159  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, cont);
3160 }
3161 
3162 // Shared routine for multiple compare operations.
3163 void VisitCompare(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
3164  InstructionOperand left, InstructionOperand right,
3165  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3166  if (cont->IsSelect()) {
3167  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3168  InstructionOperand inputs[4] = {left, right};
3169  if (cont->condition() == kUnorderedEqual) {
3170  cont->Negate();
3171  inputs[2] = g.UseRegister(cont->true_value());
3172  inputs[3] = g.Use(cont->false_value());
3173  } else {
3174  inputs[2] = g.UseRegister(cont->false_value());
3175  inputs[3] = g.Use(cont->true_value());
3176  }
3177  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, 0, nullptr, 4, inputs, cont);
3178  return;
3179  }
3180  selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, left, right, cont);
3181 }
3182 
3183 // Shared routine for multiple compare operations.
3184 void VisitCompare(InstructionSelector* selector, InstructionCode opcode,
3185  OpIndex left, OpIndex right, FlagsContinuation* cont,
3186  bool commutative) {
3187  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3188  if (commutative && g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right)) {
3189  std::swap(left, right);
3190  }
3191  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.UseRegister(left), g.Use(right), cont);
3192 }

3194 MachineType MachineTypeForNarrow(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3195  OpIndex hint_node) {
3196  if (selector->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(hint_node)) {
3197  MachineType hint = selector->load_view(hint_node).loaded_rep();
3198  int64_t constant;
3199  if (selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(node, &constant)) {
3200  if (hint == MachineType::Int8()) {
3201  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min() &&
3202  constant <= std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max()) {
3203  return hint;
3204  }
3205  } else if (hint == MachineType::Uint8()) {
3206  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min() &&
3207  constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
3208  return hint;
3209  }
3210  } else if (hint == MachineType::Int16()) {
3211  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min() &&
3212  constant <= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max()) {
3213  return hint;
3214  }
3215  } else if (hint == MachineType::Uint16()) {
3216  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::min() &&
3217  constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
3218  return hint;
3219  }
3220  } else if (hint == MachineType::Int32()) {
3221  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
3222  constant <= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()) {
3223  return hint;
3224  }
3225  } else if (hint == MachineType::Uint32()) {
3226  if (constant >= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::min() &&
3227  constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max())
3228  return hint;
3229  }
3230  }
3231  }
3232  if (selector->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(node)) {
3233  return selector->load_view(node).loaded_rep();
3234  }
3235  return MachineType::None();
3236 }
3237 
3238 bool IsIntConstant(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
3239  if (auto constant = selector->Get(node).TryCast<ConstantOp>()) {
3240  return constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32 ||
3241  constant->kind == ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64;
3242  }
3243  return false;
3244 }
3245 bool IsWordAnd(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
3246  if (auto binop = selector->Get(node).TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
3247  return binop->kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd;
3248  }
3249  return false;
3250 }
3251 
3252 // The result of WordAnd with a positive interger constant in X64 is known to
3253 // be sign(zero)-extended. Comparing this result with another positive interger
3254 // constant can have narrowed operand.
3255 MachineType MachineTypeForNarrowWordAnd(InstructionSelector* selector,
3256  OpIndex and_node,
3257  OpIndex constant_node) {
3258  const WordBinopOp& op = selector->Cast<WordBinopOp>(and_node);
3259  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
3260  auto and_left = op.left();
3261  auto and_right = op.right();
3262  auto and_constant_node = IsIntConstant(selector, and_right) ? and_right
3263  : IsIntConstant(selector, and_left) ? and_left
3264  : OpIndex{};
3265 
3266  if (and_constant_node.valid()) {
3267  int64_t and_constant, cmp_constant;
3268  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(and_constant_node, &and_constant);
3269  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(constant_node, &cmp_constant);
3270  if (and_constant >= 0 && cmp_constant >= 0) {
3271  int64_t constant =
3272  and_constant > cmp_constant ? and_constant : cmp_constant;
3273  if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max()) {
3274  return MachineType::Int8();
3275  } else if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max()) {
3276  return MachineType::Uint8();
3277  } else if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max()) {
3278  return MachineType::Int16();
3279  } else if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max()) {
3280  return MachineType::Uint16();
3281  } else if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()) {
3282  return MachineType::Int32();
3283  } else if (constant <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
3284  return MachineType::Uint32();
3285  }
3286  }
3287  }
3288 
3289  return MachineType::None();
3290 }
3291 
3292 // Tries to match the size of the given opcode to that of the operands, if
3293 // possible.
3294 InstructionCode TryNarrowOpcodeSize(InstructionSelector* selector,
3295  InstructionCode opcode, OpIndex left,
3296  OpIndex right, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3297  MachineType left_type = MachineType::None();
3298  MachineType right_type = MachineType::None();
3299  if (IsWordAnd(selector, left) && IsIntConstant(selector, right)) {
3300  left_type = MachineTypeForNarrowWordAnd(selector, left, right);
3301  right_type = left_type;
3302  } else if (IsWordAnd(selector, right) && IsIntConstant(selector, left)) {
3303  right_type = MachineTypeForNarrowWordAnd(selector, right, left);
3304  left_type = right_type;
3305  } else {
3306  // TODO(epertoso): we can probably get some size information out phi nodes.
3307  // If the load representations don't match, both operands will be
3308  // zero/sign-extended to 32bit.
3309  left_type = MachineTypeForNarrow(selector, left, right);
3310  right_type = MachineTypeForNarrow(selector, right, left);
3311  }
3312  if (left_type == right_type) {
3313  switch (left_type.representation()) {
3314  case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
3315  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8: {
3316  if (opcode == kX64Test || opcode == kX64Test32) return kX64Test8;
3317  if (opcode == kX64Cmp || opcode == kX64Cmp32) {
3318  if (left_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kUint32) {
3319  cont->OverwriteUnsignedIfSigned();
3320  } else {
3321  CHECK_EQ(MachineSemantic::kInt32, left_type.semantic());
3322  }
3323  return kX64Cmp8;
3324  }
3325  break;
3326  }
3327  // Cmp16/Test16 may introduce LCP(Length-Changing-Prefixes) stall, use
3328  // Cmp32/Test32 instead.
3329  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16: // Fall through.
3330  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3331  if (opcode == kX64Test) return kX64Test32;
3332  if (opcode == kX64Cmp) {
3333  if (left_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kUint32) {
3334  cont->OverwriteUnsignedIfSigned();
3335  } else {
3336  CHECK_EQ(MachineSemantic::kInt32, left_type.semantic());
3337  }
3338  return kX64Cmp32;
3339  }
3340  break;
3341 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
3342  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
3343  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
3344  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
3345  // When pointer compression is enabled the lower 32-bits uniquely
3346  // identify tagged value.
3347  if (opcode == kX64Cmp) return kX64Cmp32;
3348  break;
3349 #endif
3350  default:
3351  break;
3352  }
3353  }
3354  return opcode;
3355 }
3356 
3357 /*
3358 Remove unnecessary WordAnd
3359 For example:
3360 33: IfFalse(31)
3361 517: Int32Constant[65535]
3362 518: Word32And(18, 517)
3363 36: Int32Constant[266]
3364 37: Int32LessThanOrEqual(36, 518)
3365 38: Branch[None]
3366 
3367 If Int32LessThanOrEqual select cmp16, the above Word32And can be removed:
3368 33: IfFalse(31)
3369 36: Int32Constant[266]
3370 37: Int32LessThanOrEqual(36, 18)
3371 38: Branch[None]
3372 */
3373 OpIndex RemoveUnnecessaryWordAnd(InstructionSelector* selector,
3374  InstructionCode opcode, OpIndex and_node) {
3375  int64_t mask = 0;
3376 
3377  if (opcode == kX64Cmp32 || opcode == kX64Test32) {
3378  mask = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max();
3379  } else if (opcode == kX64Cmp16 || opcode == kX64Test16) {
3380  mask = std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
3381  } else if (opcode == kX64Cmp8 || opcode == kX64Test8) {
3382  mask = std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max();
3383  } else {
3384  return and_node;
3385  }
3386 
3387  const WordBinopOp& op = selector->Cast<WordBinopOp>(and_node);
3388  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
3389  auto and_left = op.left();
3390  auto and_right = op.right();
3391  auto and_constant_node = OpIndex{};
3392  auto and_other_node = OpIndex{};
3393  if (IsIntConstant(selector, and_left)) {
3394  and_constant_node = and_left;
3395  and_other_node = and_right;
3396  } else if (IsIntConstant(selector, and_right)) {
3397  and_constant_node = and_right;
3398  and_other_node = and_left;
3399  }
3400 
3401  if (and_constant_node.valid()) {
3402  int64_t and_constant;
3403  selector->MatchSignedIntegralConstant(and_constant_node, &and_constant);
3404  if (and_constant == mask) return and_other_node;
3405  }
3406  return and_node;
3407 }
3408 
3409 // Shared routine for multiple word compare operations.
3410 void VisitWordCompare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3411  InstructionCode opcode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3412  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3413  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
3414  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
3415  auto left = op.input(0);
3416  auto right = op.input(1);
3417 
3418  // The 32-bit comparisons automatically truncate Word64
3419  // values to Word32 range, no need to do that explicitly.
3420  if (opcode == kX64Cmp32 || opcode == kX64Test32) {
3421  if (V<Word64> left64;
3422  selector->MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(left, &left64)) {
3423  left = left64;
3424  }
3425  if (V<Word64> right64;
3426  selector->MatchTruncateWord64ToWord32(right, &right64)) {
3427  right = right64;
3428  }
3429  }
3430 
3431  opcode = TryNarrowOpcodeSize(selector, opcode, left, right, cont);
3432 
3433  // If one of the two inputs is an immediate, make sure it's on the right, or
3434  // if one of the two inputs is a memory operand, make sure it's on the left.
3435  int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
3436 
3437  if ((!g.CanBeImmediate(right) && g.CanBeImmediate(left)) ||
3438  (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, right, effect_level) &&
3439  !g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, left, effect_level))) {
3440  if (!selector->IsCommutative(node)) cont->Commute();
3441  std::swap(left, right);
3442  }
3443 
3444  if (IsWordAnd(selector, left)) {
3445  left = RemoveUnnecessaryWordAnd(selector, opcode, left);
3446  }
3447 
3448  // Match immediates on right side of comparison.
3449  if (g.CanBeImmediate(right)) {
3450  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, left, effect_level)) {
3451  return VisitCompareWithMemoryOperand(selector, opcode, left,
3452  g.UseImmediate(right), cont);
3453  }
3454  return VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.Use(left), g.UseImmediate(right),
3455  cont);
3456  }
3457 
3458  // Match memory operands on left side of comparison.
3459  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, left, effect_level)) {
3460  return VisitCompareWithMemoryOperand(selector, opcode, left,
3461  g.UseRegister(right), cont);
3462  }
3463 
3464  return VisitCompare(selector, opcode, left, right, cont,
3465  selector->IsCommutative(node));
3466 }
3467 
3468 void VisitWord64EqualImpl(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3469  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3470  if (selector->CanUseRootsRegister()) {
3471  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3472  const RootsTable& roots_table = selector->isolate()->roots_table();
3473  RootIndex root_index;
3474  const ComparisonOp& equal =
3475  selector->Get(node).template Cast<ComparisonOp>();
3476  DCHECK_EQ(equal.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual);
3477  Handle<HeapObject> object;
3478  if (equal.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged() &&
3479  selector->MatchHeapConstant(equal.right(), &object)) {
3480  if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(object, &root_index)) {
3481  InstructionCode opcode =
3482  kX64Cmp | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
3483  return VisitCompare(
3484  selector, opcode,
3485  g.TempImmediate(
3486  MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(root_index)),
3487  g.UseRegister(equal.left()), cont);
3488  }
3489  }
3490  }
3491  VisitWordCompare(selector, node, kX64Cmp, cont);
3492 }
3493 
3494 bool MatchHeapObjectEqual(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3495  OpIndex* left, Handle<HeapObject>* right) {
3496  const ComparisonOp& equal = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3497  DCHECK_EQ(equal.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual);
3498  if (selector->MatchHeapConstant(equal.right(), right)) {
3499  *left = equal.left();
3500  return true;
3501  }
3502  return false;
3503 }
3504 
3505 void VisitWord32EqualImpl(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3506  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3507  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && selector->isolate()) {
3508  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3509  const RootsTable& roots_table = selector->isolate()->roots_table();
3510  RootIndex root_index;
3511  OpIndex left;
3512  Handle<HeapObject> right;
3513  // HeapConstants and CompressedHeapConstants can be treated the same when
3514  // using them as an input to a 32-bit comparison. Check whether either is
3515  // present.
3516  if (MatchHeapObjectEqual(selector, node, &left, &right)) {
3517  if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(right, &root_index)) {
3518  DCHECK(left.valid());
3519  if (RootsTable::IsReadOnly(root_index) &&
3520  (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL || !selector->isolate()->bootstrapper())) {
3521  return VisitCompare(
3522  selector, kX64Cmp32, g.UseRegister(left),
3523  g.TempImmediate(MacroAssemblerBase::ReadOnlyRootPtr(
3524  root_index, selector->isolate())),
3525  cont);
3526  }
3527  if (selector->CanUseRootsRegister()) {
3528  InstructionCode opcode =
3529  kX64Cmp32 | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_Root);
3530  return VisitCompare(
3531  selector, opcode,
3532  g.TempImmediate(
3533  MacroAssemblerBase::RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(
3534  root_index)),
3535  g.UseRegister(left), cont);
3536  }
3537  }
3538  }
3539  }
3540  VisitWordCompare(selector, node, kX64Cmp32, cont);
3541 }
3542 
3543 void VisitCompareZero(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex user, OpIndex node,
3544  InstructionCode opcode, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3545  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3546  const Operation& op = selector->turboshaft_graph()->Get(node);
3547  if (cont->IsBranch() &&
3548  (cont->condition() == kNotEqual || cont->condition() == kEqual)) {
3549  if (const WordBinopOp* binop = op.TryCast<WordBinopOp>()) {
3550  if (selector->IsOnlyUserOfNodeInSameBlock(user, node)) {
3551  const bool is64 = binop->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
3552  switch (binop->kind) {
3553  case WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd:
3554  return VisitBinop(selector, node, is64 ? kX64Add : kX64Add32, cont);
3555  case WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub:
3556  return VisitBinop(selector, node, is64 ? kX64Sub : kX64Sub32, cont);
3557  case WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd:
3558  return VisitBinop(selector, node, is64 ? kX64And : kX64And32, cont);
3559  case WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr:
3560  return VisitBinop(selector, node, is64 ? kX64Or : kX64Or32, cont);
3561  default:
3562  break;
3563  }
3564  }
3565  } else if (const ShiftOp* shift = op.TryCast<ShiftOp>()) {
3566  if (selector->IsOnlyUserOfNodeInSameBlock(user, node)) {
3567  const bool is64 = shift->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
3568  switch (shift->kind) {
3569  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft:
3570  if (TryVisitWordShift(selector, node, is64 ? 64 : 32,
3571  is64 ? kX64Shl : kX64Shl32, cont)) {
3572  return;
3573  }
3574  break;
3575  case ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical:
3576  if (TryVisitWordShift(selector, node, is64 ? 64 : 32,
3577  is64 ? kX64Shr : kX64Shr32, cont)) {
3578  return;
3579  }
3580  break;
3581  default:
3582  break;
3583  }
3584  }
3585  }
3586  }
3587 
3588  int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
3589  if (const auto load = op.TryCast<LoadOp>()) {
3590  if (load->loaded_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8() ||
3591  load->loaded_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()) {
3592  if (opcode == kX64Cmp32) {
3593  opcode = kX64Cmp8;
3594  } else if (opcode == kX64Test32) {
3595  opcode = kX64Test8;
3596  }
3597  } else if (load->loaded_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int16() ||
3598  load->loaded_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint16()) {
3599  if (opcode == kX64Cmp32) {
3600  opcode = kX64Cmp16;
3601  } else if (opcode == kX64Test32) {
3602  opcode = kX64Test16;
3603  }
3604  }
3605  }
3606  if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, user, node, effect_level)) {
3607  VisitCompareWithMemoryOperand(selector, opcode, node, g.TempImmediate(0),
3608  cont);
3609  } else {
3610  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.Use(node), g.TempImmediate(0), cont);
3611  }
3612 }
3613 
3614 // Shared routine for multiple float32 compare operations (inputs commuted).
3615 void VisitFloat32Compare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3616  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3617  const ComparisonOp& op = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3618  InstructionCode const opcode =
3619  selector->IsSupported(AVX) ? kAVXFloat32Cmp : kSSEFloat32Cmp;
3620  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, op.right(), op.left(), cont, false);
3621 }
3622 
3623 // Shared routine for multiple float64 compare operations (inputs commuted).
3624 void VisitFloat64Compare(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3625  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3626  const ComparisonOp& op = selector->Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3627  InstructionCode const opcode =
3628  selector->IsSupported(AVX) ? kAVXFloat64Cmp : kSSEFloat64Cmp;
3629  VisitCompare(selector, opcode, op.right(), op.left(), cont, false);
3630 }

3632 // Shared routine for Word32/Word64 Atomic Binops
3633 void VisitAtomicBinop(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3634  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
3635  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
3636  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
3637  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3638  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
3639  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
3640  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.value()),
3641  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.base()),
3642  g.GetEffectiveIndexOperand(atomic_op.index(), &addressing_mode)};
3643  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsFixed(node, rax)};
3644  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
3645  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3646  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3647  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3648  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3649  }
3650  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs,
3651  arraysize(temps), temps);
3652 }
3653 
3654 // Shared routine for Word32/Word64 Atomic CmpExchg
3655 void VisitAtomicCompareExchange(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
3656  ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width,
3657  MemoryAccessKind access_kind) {
3658  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = selector->Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
3659  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
3660  AddressingMode addressing_mode;
3661  InstructionOperand inputs[] = {
3662  g.UseFixed(atomic_op.expected().value(), rax),
3663  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.value()),
3664  g.UseUniqueRegister(atomic_op.base()),
3665  g.GetEffectiveIndexOperand(atomic_op.index(), &addressing_mode)};
3666  InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsFixed(node, rax)};
3667  InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3668  AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3669  if (access_kind == MemoryAccessKind::kProtectedByTrapHandler) {
3670  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
3671  }
3672  selector->Emit(code, arraysize(outputs), outputs, arraysize(inputs), inputs);
3673 }

3675 } // namespace
3676 
3677 // Shared routine for word comparison against zero.
3678 void InstructionSelector::VisitWordCompareZero(OpIndex user, OpIndex value,
3679  FlagsContinuation* cont) {
3680  // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
3681  ConsumeEqualZero(&user, &value, cont);
3682 
3683  if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3684  const Operation& value_op = Get(value);
3685  if (const ComparisonOp* comparison = value_op.TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
3686  if (comparison->kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual) {
3687  switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
3688  case RegisterRepresentation::Word32():
3689  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3690  return VisitWord32EqualImpl(this, value, cont);
3691  case RegisterRepresentation::Word64(): {
3692  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3693  if (this->MatchIntegralZero(comparison->right())) {
3694  // Try to combine the branch with a comparison.
3695  if (CanCover(value, comparison->left())) {
3696  const Operation& left_op = this->Get(comparison->left());
3697  if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Sub>()) {
3698  return VisitWordCompare(this, comparison->left(), kX64Cmp,
3699  cont);
3700  } else if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
3701  return VisitWordCompare(this, comparison->left(), kX64Test,
3702  cont);
3703  }
3704  }
3705  return VisitCompareZero(this, value, comparison->left(), kX64Cmp,
3706  cont);
3707  }
3708  return VisitWord64EqualImpl(this, value, cont);
3709  }
3710  case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
3711  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnorderedEqual);
3712  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3713  case RegisterRepresentation::Float64(): {
3714  bool is_self_compare = comparison->left() == comparison->right();
3715  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(is_self_compare ? kIsNotNaN
3716  : kUnorderedEqual);
3717  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3718  }
3719  default:
3720  break;
3721  }
3722  } else {
3723  switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
3724  case RegisterRepresentation::Word32(): {
3725  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3726  GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
3727  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kX64Cmp32, cont);
3728  }
3729  case RegisterRepresentation::Word64(): {
3730  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3731  GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
3732  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kX64Cmp, cont);
3733  }
3734  case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
3735  if (comparison->kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan) {
3736  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedGreaterThan);
3737  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3738  } else {
3739  DCHECK_EQ(comparison->kind,
3740  ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual);
3741  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual);
3742  return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3743  }
3744  case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
3745  if (comparison->kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan) {
3746  if (MatchZero(comparison->left())) {
3747  const Operation& right = this->Get(comparison->right());
3748  if (right.Is<Opmask::kFloat64Abs>()) {
3749  // This matches the pattern
3750  //
3751  // Float64LessThan(#0.0, Float64Abs(x))
3752  //
3753  // which TurboFan generates for NumberToBoolean in the general
3754  // case, and which evaluates to false if x is 0, -0 or NaN. We
3755  // can compile this to a simple (v)ucomisd using not_equal
3756  // flags condition, which avoids the costly Float64Abs.
3757  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3758  InstructionCode const opcode =
3759  IsSupported(AVX) ? kAVXFloat64Cmp : kSSEFloat64Cmp;
3760  return VisitCompare(this, opcode, comparison->left(),
3761  right.Cast<FloatUnaryOp>().input(), cont,
3762  false);
3763  }
3764  }
3765  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedGreaterThan);
3766  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3767  } else {
3768  DCHECK_EQ(comparison->kind,
3769  ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual);
3770  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual);
3771  return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3772  }
3773  default:
3774  break;
3775  }
3776  }
3777  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
3778  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kX64Cmp32, cont);
3779  } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
3780  return VisitWordCompare(this, value, kX64Test32, cont);
3781  } else if (const ProjectionOp* projection =
3782  value_op.TryCast<ProjectionOp>()) {
3783  // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
3784  // OverflowCheckedBinop operation.
3785  if (projection->index == 1u) {
3786  // We cannot combine the OverflowCheckedBinop operation with this branch
3787  // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
3788  // operation is either {OpIndex::Invalid()}, which means there's no use
3789  // of the actual value, or was already defined, which means it is
3790  // scheduled *AFTER* this branch).
3791  OpIndex node = projection->input();
3792  if (const OverflowCheckedBinopOp* binop =
3793  this->TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node);
3794  binop && CanDoBranchIfOverflowFusion(node)) {
3795  const bool is64 = binop->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
3796  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3797  switch (binop->kind) {
3798  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd:
3799  return VisitBinop(this, node, is64 ? kX64Add : kX64Add32, cont);
3800  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub:
3801  return VisitBinop(this, node, is64 ? kX64Sub : kX64Sub32, cont);
3802  case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
3803  return VisitBinop(this, node, is64 ? kX64Imul : kX64Imul32, cont);
3804  }
3805  UNREACHABLE();
3806  }
3807  }
3808  } else if (value_op.Is<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>()) {
3809  cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
3810  return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
3811  }
3812  }
3813 
3814  // Branch could not be combined with a compare, emit compare against 0.
3815  VisitCompareZero(this, user, value, kX64Cmp32, cont);
3816 }
3817 
3818 void InstructionSelector::VisitSwitch(OpIndex node, const SwitchInfo& sw) {
3819  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
3820  const SwitchOp& op = Cast<SwitchOp>(node);
3821  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
3822  InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(op.input());
3823 
3824  // Emit either ArchTableSwitch or ArchBinarySearchSwitch.
3825  if (enable_switch_jump_table_) {
3826  static const size_t kMaxTableSwitchValueRange = 2 << 16;
3827  size_t table_space_cost = 4 + sw.value_range();
3828  size_t table_time_cost = 3;
3829  size_t lookup_space_cost = 3 + 2 * sw.case_count();
3830  size_t lookup_time_cost = sw.case_count();
3831  if (sw.case_count() > 4 &&
3832  table_space_cost + 3 * table_time_cost <=
3833  lookup_space_cost + 3 * lookup_time_cost &&
3834  sw.min_value() > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
3835  sw.value_range() <= kMaxTableSwitchValueRange) {
3836  InstructionOperand index_operand = g.TempRegister();
3837  if (sw.min_value()) {
3838  // The leal automatically zero extends, so result is a valid 64-bit
3839  // index.
3840  Emit(kX64Lea32 | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI), index_operand,
3841  value_operand, g.TempImmediate(-sw.min_value()));
3842  } else {
3843  // Zero extend, because we use it as 64-bit index into the jump table.
3844  if (ZeroExtendsWord32ToWord64(op.input())) {
3845  // Input value has already been zero-extended.
3846  index_operand = value_operand;
3847  } else {
3848  Emit(kX64Movl, index_operand, value_operand);
3849  }
3850  }
3851  // Generate a table lookup.
3852  return EmitTableSwitch(sw, index_operand);
3853  }
3854  }
3855 
3856  // Generate a tree of conditional jumps.
3857  return EmitBinarySearchSwitch(sw, value_operand);
3858 }
3859 
3860 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32Equal(OpIndex node) {
3861  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kEqual, node);
3862  const ComparisonOp& equal = Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3863  DCHECK_EQ(equal.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual);
3864  DCHECK(equal.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32() ||
3865  equal.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
3866  if (MatchIntegralZero(equal.right())) {
3867  return VisitWordCompareZero(node, equal.left(), &cont);
3868  }
3869  VisitWord32EqualImpl(this, node, &cont);
3870 }
3871 
3872 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32LessThan(OpIndex node) {
3873  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kSignedLessThan, node);
3874  VisitWordCompare(this, node, kX64Cmp32, &cont);
3875 }

3894 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord64Equal(OpIndex node) {
3895  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kEqual, node);
3896  const ComparisonOp& equal = Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3897  DCHECK_EQ(equal.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual);
3898  DCHECK(equal.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word64() ||
3899  equal.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
3900  if (MatchIntegralZero(equal.right())) {
3901  if (CanCover(node, equal.left())) {
3902  const Operation& left_op = Get(equal.left());
3903  if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Sub>()) {
3904  return VisitWordCompare(this, equal.left(), kX64Cmp, &cont);
3905  } else if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
3906  return VisitWordCompare(this, equal.left(), kX64Test, &cont);
3907  }
3908  }
3909  }
3910  VisitWord64EqualImpl(this, node, &cont);
3911 }
3912 
3913 void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32AddWithOverflow(OpIndex node) {
3914  OptionalOpIndex ovf = FindProjection(node, 1);
3915  if (ovf.valid()) {
3916  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kOverflow, ovf.value());
3917  return VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add32, &cont);
3918  }
3919  FlagsContinuation cont;
3920  VisitBinop(this, node, kX64Add32, &cont);
3921 }

3972 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64Equal(OpIndex node) {
3973  const ComparisonOp& op = Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3974  bool is_self_compare = op.left() == op.right();
3975  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(
3976  is_self_compare ? kIsNotNaN : kUnorderedEqual, node);
3977  VisitFloat64Compare(this, node, &cont);
3978 }
3979 
3980 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64LessThan(OpIndex node) {
3981  // Check for the pattern
3982  //
3983  // Float64LessThan(#0.0, Float64Abs(x))
3984  //
3985  // which TurboFan generates for NumberToBoolean in the general case,
3986  // and which evaluates to false if x is 0, -0 or NaN. We can compile
3987  // this to a simple (v)ucomisd using not_equal flags condition, which
3988  // avoids the costly Float64Abs.
3989  const ComparisonOp& cmp = Cast<ComparisonOp>(node);
3990  DCHECK_EQ(cmp.rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
3991  DCHECK_EQ(cmp.kind, ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan);
3992  if (MatchZero(cmp.left())) {
3993  if (const FloatUnaryOp* right_op =
3994  TryCast<Opmask::kFloat64Abs>(cmp.right())) {
3995  FlagsContinuation cont = FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kNotEqual, node);
3996  InstructionCode const opcode =
3997  IsSupported(AVX) ? kAVXFloat64Cmp : kSSEFloat64Cmp;
3998  return VisitCompare(this, opcode, cmp.left(), right_op->input(), &cont,
3999  false);
4000  }
4001  }
4002  FlagsContinuation cont =
4003  FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kUnsignedGreaterThan, node);
4004  VisitFloat64Compare(this, node, &cont);
4005 }
4006 
4007 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64LessThanOrEqual(OpIndex node) {
4008  FlagsContinuation cont =
4009  FlagsContinuation::ForSet(kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual, node);
4010  VisitFloat64Compare(this, node, &cont);
4011 }
4012 
4013 void InstructionSelector::VisitBitcastWord32PairToFloat64(OpIndex node) {
4014  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4015  const auto& bitcast = Cast<BitcastWord32PairToFloat64Op>(node);
4016  OpIndex hi = bitcast.high_word32();
4017  OpIndex lo = bitcast.low_word32();
4018 
4019  // TODO(nicohartmann@): We could try to emit a better sequence here.
4020  InstructionOperand zero = sequence()->AddImmediate(Constant(0.0));
4021  InstructionOperand temp = g.TempDoubleRegister();
4022  Emit(kSSEFloat64InsertHighWord32, temp, zero, g.Use(hi));
4023  Emit(kSSEFloat64InsertLowWord32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), temp, g.Use(lo));
4024 }
4025 
4026 void InstructionSelector::VisitFloat64SilenceNaN(OpIndex node) {
4027  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4028  const FloatUnaryOp& op = Cast<FloatUnaryOp>(node);
4029  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
4030  Emit(kSSEFloat64SilenceNaN, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
4031  g.UseRegister(op.input()));
4032 }
4033 
4034 void InstructionSelector::VisitMemoryBarrier(OpIndex node) {
4035  AtomicMemoryOrder order;
4036  order = Cast<MemoryBarrierOp>(node).memory_order;
4037  // x64 is no weaker than release-acquire and only needs to emit an
4038  // instruction for SeqCst memory barriers.
4039  if (order == AtomicMemoryOrder::kSeqCst) {
4040  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4041  Emit(kX64MFence, g.NoOutput());
4042  return;
4043  }
4044  DCHECK_EQ(AtomicMemoryOrder::kAcqRel, order);
4045 }

4047 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32AtomicLoad(OpIndex node) {
4048  LoadRepresentation load_rep = load_view(node).loaded_rep();
4049  DCHECK(IsIntegral(load_rep.representation()) ||
4050  IsAnyTagged(load_rep.representation()) ||
4051  (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL &&
4052  CanBeCompressedPointer(load_rep.representation())));
4053  DCHECK_NE(load_rep.representation(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4054  DCHECK(!load_rep.IsMapWord());
4055  // The memory order is ignored as both acquire and sequentially consistent
4056  // loads can emit MOV.
4057  // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
4058  VisitLoad(node, node, GetLoadOpcode(load_rep));
4059 }
4060

4063  DCHECK(!load_rep.IsMapWord());
4064  // The memory order is ignored as both acquire and sequentially consistent
4065  // loads can emit MOV.
4066  // https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~pes20/cpp/cpp0xmappings.html
4067  VisitLoad(node, node, GetLoadOpcode(load_rep));
4068 }

4088 void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32AtomicExchange(OpIndex node) {
4089  const AtomicRMWOp& atomic_op = Cast<AtomicRMWOp>(node);
4090  ArchOpcode opcode;
4091  if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int8()) {
4092  opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt8;
4093  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint8()) {
4094  opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint8;
4095  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int16()) {
4096  opcode = kAtomicExchangeInt16;
4097  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint16()) {
4098  opcode = kAtomicExchangeUint16;
4099  } else if (atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Int32() ||
4100  atomic_op.memory_rep == MemoryRepresentation::Uint32()) {
4101  opcode = kAtomicExchangeWord32;
4102  } else {
4103  UNREACHABLE();
4104  }
4105  VisitAtomicExchange(this, node, opcode, AtomicWidth::kWord32,
4106  atomic_op.memory_access_kind);
4107 }

4535 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128Const(OpIndex node) {
4536  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4537  static const int kUint32Immediates = kSimd128Size / sizeof(uint32_t);
4538  uint32_t val[kUint32Immediates];
4539  const Simd128ConstantOp& constant = Cast<Simd128ConstantOp>(node);
4540  memcpy(val, constant.value, kSimd128Size);
4541  // If all bytes are zeros or ones, avoid emitting code for generic constants
4542  bool all_zeros = !(val[0] || val[1] || val[2] || val[3]);
4543  bool all_ones = val[0] == UINT32_MAX && val[1] == UINT32_MAX &&
4544  val[2] == UINT32_MAX && val[3] == UINT32_MAX;
4545  InstructionOperand dst = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
4546  if (all_zeros) {
4547  Emit(kX64SZero | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), dst);
4548  } else if (all_ones) {
4549  Emit(kX64SAllOnes | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), dst);
4550  } else {
4551  Emit(kX64S128Const, dst, g.UseImmediate(val[0]), g.UseImmediate(val[1]),
4552  g.UseImmediate(val[2]), g.UseImmediate(val[3]));
4553  }
4554 }
4555 
4556 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128Zero(OpIndex node) {
4557  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4558  Emit(kX64SZero | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), g.DefineAsRegister(node));
4559 }

4561 #define SIMD_INT_TYPES_FOR_SPLAT(V) \

4568  V(I16x16, kL16, kV256) \
4569  V(I8x32, kL8, kV256)
4570 
4571 // Splat with an optimization for const 0.
4572 #define VISIT_INT_SIMD_SPLAT(Type, LaneSize, VectorLength) \
4573  void InstructionSelector::Visit##Type##Splat(OpIndex node) { \
4574  X64OperandGenerator g(this); \
4575  const Operation& op = Get(node); \
4576  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1); \
4577  OpIndex input = op.input(0); \
4578  if (g.CanBeImmediate(input) && g.GetImmediateIntegerValue(input) == 0) { \
4579  Emit(kX64SZero | VectorLengthField::encode(VectorLength), \
4580  g.DefineAsRegister(node)); \
4581  } else { \
4582  Emit(kX64ISplat | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize) | \
4583  VectorLengthField::encode(VectorLength), \
4584  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(input)); \
4585  } \
4586  }
4587 SIMD_INT_TYPES_FOR_SPLAT(VISIT_INT_SIMD_SPLAT)
4588 #undef VISIT_INT_SIMD_SPLAT
4589 #undef SIMD_INT_TYPES_FOR_SPLAT

4595  Emit(kX64FSplat | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
4596  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
4597  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.Use(op.input()));

4648  int32_t lane = op.lane; \

4650  VectorLengthField::encode(VectorLength), \

4652  g.UseImmediate(lane)); \
4653  }

4696 void InstructionSelector::VisitF64x2ReplaceLane(OpIndex node) {
4697  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4698  // When no-AVX, define dst == src to save a move.
4699  InstructionOperand dst =
4700  IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
4701  const Simd128ReplaceLaneOp& op = Cast<Simd128ReplaceLaneOp>(node);
4702  Emit(kX64FReplaceLane | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
4703  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
4704  dst, g.UseRegister(op.into()), g.UseImmediate(op.lane),
4705  g.UseRegister(op.new_lane()));
4706 }

4712  Emit(OPCODE, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.into()), \
4713  g.UseImmediate(op.lane), g.Use(op.new_lane())); \
4714  }

4726 #define VISIT_SIMD_SHIFT_LANE_SIZE_VECTOR_LENGTH_OPCODES( \
4727  Name, Opcode, LaneSize, VectorLength) \
4728  void InstructionSelector::Visit##Name(OpIndex node) { \
4729  X64OperandGenerator g(this); \
4730  const Operation& op = Get(node); \
4731  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2); \
4732  InstructionOperand dst = IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) \
4733  : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node); \
4734  if (g.CanBeImmediate(op.input(1))) { \
4735  Emit(kX64##Opcode | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize) | \
4736  VectorLengthField::encode(VectorLength), \
4737  dst, g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseImmediate(op.input(1))); \
4738  } else { \
4739  Emit(kX64##Opcode | LaneSizeField::encode(LaneSize) | \
4740  VectorLengthField::encode(VectorLength), \
4741  dst, g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseRegister(op.input(1))); \
4742  } \
4743  }

4890 static bool IsV128ZeroConst(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node) {
4891  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
4892  if (auto constant = op.TryCast<Simd128ConstantOp>()) {
4893  return constant->IsZero();
4894  }
4895  return false;
4896 }
4897 
4898 static bool MatchSimd128Constant(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
4899  std::array<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>* constant) {
4900  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(constant);
4901  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
4902  if (auto c = op.TryCast<Simd128ConstantOp>()) {
4903  std::memcpy(constant, c->value, kSimd128Size);
4904  return true;
4905  }
4906  return false;
4907 }

4910 
4911 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128Select(OpIndex node) {
4912  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4913  const Simd128TernaryOp& op = Cast<Simd128TernaryOp>(node);
4914  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 3);
4915 
4916  InstructionOperand dst =
4917  IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
4918  if (IsV128ZeroConst(this, op.input(2))) {
4919  // select(cond, input1, 0) -> and(cond, input1)
4920  Emit(kX64SAnd | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), dst,
4921  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseRegister(op.input(1)));
4922  } else if (IsV128ZeroConst(this, op.input(1))) {
4923  // select(cond, 0, input2) -> and(not(cond), input2)
4924  Emit(kX64SAndNot | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), dst,
4925  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseRegister(op.input(2)));
4926  } else {
4927  Emit(kX64SSelect | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128), dst,
4928  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseRegister(op.input(1)),
4929  g.UseRegister(op.input(2)));
4930  }
4931 }
4932

4938  g.UseRegister(op.input(0)), g.UseRegister(op.input(1)),
4939  g.UseRegister(op.input(2)));
4940 #else
4941  UNREACHABLE();
4942 #endif

4945 void InstructionSelector::VisitS128AndNot(OpIndex node) {
4946  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4947  const Simd128BinopOp& op = Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(node);
4948  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
4949  // andnps a b does ~a & b, but we want a & !b, so flip the input.
4950  Emit(kX64SAndNot | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
4951  IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
4952  g.UseRegister(op.right()), g.UseRegister(op.left()));
4953 }

4985 void InstructionSelector::VisitF32x4UConvertI32x4(OpIndex node) {
4986  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
4987  const Simd128UnaryOp& op = Cast<Simd128UnaryOp>(node);
4988  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
4989  OpIndex value = op.input();
4990 
4991  // F32x4SConvertI32x4 is more efficient than F32x4UConvertI32x4 on x64,
4992  // if the u32x4 input can fit into i32x4, we can use F32x4SConvertI32x4
4993  // instead. Input node with I32x4UConvertI16x8Low/I32x4UConvertI16x8High
4994  // opcode is one of this kinds.
4995  bool can_use_sign_convert = false;
4996  if (const Simd128UnaryOp* unop =
4997  this->Get(value).template TryCast<Simd128UnaryOp>()) {
4998  if (unop->kind == Simd128UnaryOp::Kind::kI32x4UConvertI16x8Low ||
4999  unop->kind == Simd128UnaryOp::Kind::kI32x4UConvertI16x8High) {
5000  can_use_sign_convert = true;
5001  }
5002  }
5003 
5004  if (can_use_sign_convert) {
5005  Emit(kX64F32x4SConvertI32x4, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
5006  g.UseRegister(op.input()));
5007  } else {
5008  Emit(kX64F32x4UConvertI32x4, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
5009  g.UseRegister(op.input()));
5010  }
5011 }

5049  void InstructionSelector::VisitI64x2Neg(OpIndex node) {
5050  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5051  const Simd128UnaryOp& op = Cast<Simd128UnaryOp>(node);
5052  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
5053  // If AVX unsupported, make sure dst != src to avoid a move.
5054  InstructionOperand operand0 = IsSupported(AVX)
5055  ? g.UseRegister(op.input())
5056  : g.UseUniqueRegister(op.input());
5057  Emit(
5058  kX64INeg | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) | VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
5059  g.DefineAsRegister(node), operand0);
5060 }

5062 void InstructionSelector::VisitI64x2ShrS(OpIndex node) {
5063  X64OperandGenerator g(this);

5065  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);

5067  IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);

5073  } else {
5074  InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempSimd128Register()};
5075  Emit(kX64IShrS | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
5076  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
5077  dst, g.UseUniqueRegister(op.input()), g.UseRegister(op.shift()),
5078  arraysize(temps), temps);
5079  }

5176 void InstructionSelector::VisitExtractF128(OpIndex node) {
5177  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5178  const Simd256Extract128LaneOp& op = Cast<Simd256Extract128LaneOp>(node);
5179  if (op.lane == 0) {
5180  EmitIdentity(node);
5181  } else {
5182  Emit(kX64ExtractF128, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input()),
5183  g.UseImmediate(op.lane));
5184  }
5185 }

5188 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WASM_SIMD256_REVEC

5199 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5200 namespace {
5201 
5202 // Returns true if shuffle can be decomposed into two 16x4 half shuffles
5203 // followed by a 16x8 blend.
5204 // E.g. [3 2 1 0 15 14 13 12].
5205 bool TryMatch16x8HalfShuffle(uint8_t* shuffle16x8, uint8_t* blend_mask) {
5206  *blend_mask = 0;
5207  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
5208  if ((shuffle16x8[i] & 0x4) != (i & 0x4)) return false;
5209  *blend_mask |= (shuffle16x8[i] > 7 ? 1 : 0) << i;
5210  }
5211  return true;
5212 }
5213 
5214 bool TryMatchShufps(const uint8_t* shuffle32x4) {
5215  DCHECK_GT(8, shuffle32x4[2]);
5216  DCHECK_GT(8, shuffle32x4[3]);
5217  // shufps can be used if the first 2 indices select the first input [0-3], and
5218  // the other 2 indices select the second input [4-7].
5219  return shuffle32x4[0] < 4 && shuffle32x4[1] < 4 && shuffle32x4[2] > 3 &&
5220  shuffle32x4[3] > 3;
5221 }
5222 
5223 static bool TryMatchOneInputIsZeros(InstructionSelector* selector,
5224  InstructionSelector::SimdShuffleView& view,
5225  uint8_t* shuffle, bool* needs_swap) {
5226  *needs_swap = false;
5227  bool input0_is_zero = IsV128ZeroConst(selector, view.input(0));
5228  bool input1_is_zero = IsV128ZeroConst(selector, view.input(1));
5229  if (!input0_is_zero && !input1_is_zero) {
5230  return false;
5231  }
5232 
5233  if (input0_is_zero) {
5234  *needs_swap = true;
5235  }
5236  return true;
5237 }
5238 
5239 } // namespace
5240 
5241 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x16Shuffle(OpIndex node) {
5242  uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size];
5243  bool is_swizzle;
5244  auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
5245  CanonicalizeShuffle(view, shuffle, &is_swizzle);
5246 
5247  int imm_count = 0;
5248  static const int kMaxImms = 6;
5249  uint32_t imms[kMaxImms];
5250  int temp_count = 0;
5251  static const int kMaxTemps = 2;
5252  InstructionOperand temps[kMaxTemps];
5253 
5254  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5255  // Swizzles don't generally need DefineSameAsFirst to avoid a move.
5256  bool no_same_as_first = is_swizzle;
5257  // We generally need UseRegister for input0, Use for input1.
5258  // TODO(v8:9198): We don't have 16-byte alignment for SIMD operands yet, but
5259  // we retain this logic (continue setting these in the various shuffle match
5260  // clauses), but ignore it when selecting registers or slots.
5261  bool src0_needs_reg = true;
5262  bool src1_needs_reg = false;
5263  ArchOpcode opcode = kX64I8x16Shuffle; // general shuffle is the default
5264 
5265  uint8_t offset;
5266  uint8_t shuffle32x4[4];
5267  uint8_t shuffle16x8[8];
5268  int index;
5269  const wasm::ShuffleEntry<kSimd128Size>* arch_shuffle;
5270  bool needs_swap;
5271  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchConcat(shuffle, &offset)) {
5272  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x4Rotate(shuffle, shuffle32x4,
5273  is_swizzle)) {
5274  uint8_t shuffle_mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackShuffle4(shuffle32x4);
5275  opcode = kX64S32x4Rotate;
5276  imms[imm_count++] = shuffle_mask;
5277  } else {
5278  // Swap inputs from the normal order for (v)palignr.
5279  SwapShuffleInputs(view);
5280  is_swizzle = false; // It's simpler to just handle the general case.
5281  no_same_as_first = CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX);
5282  // TODO(v8:9608): also see v8:9083
5283  src1_needs_reg = true;
5284  opcode = kX64S8x16Alignr;
5285  // palignr takes a single imm8 offset.
5286  imms[imm_count++] = offset;
5287  }
5288  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchArchShuffle(shuffle, is_swizzle,
5289  &arch_shuffle)) {
5290  opcode = arch_shuffle->opcode;
5291  src0_needs_reg = arch_shuffle->src0_needs_reg;
5292  // SSE can't take advantage of both operands in registers and needs
5293  // same-as-first.
5294  src1_needs_reg = arch_shuffle->src1_needs_reg;
5295  no_same_as_first =
5296  IsSupported(AVX) && arch_shuffle->no_same_as_first_if_avx;
5297  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch32x4Shuffle(shuffle, shuffle32x4)) {
5298  uint8_t shuffle_mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackShuffle4(shuffle32x4);
5299  if (is_swizzle) {
5300  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchIdentity(shuffle)) {
5301  // Bypass normal shuffle code generation in this case.
5302  OpIndex input = view.input(0);
5303  // EmitIdentity
5304  MarkAsUsed(input);
5305  MarkAsDefined(node);
5306  SetRename(node, input);
5307  return;
5308  } else {
5309  // pshufd takes a single imm8 shuffle mask.
5310  opcode = kX64S32x4Swizzle;
5311  no_same_as_first = true;
5312  // TODO(v8:9083): This doesn't strictly require a register, forcing the
5313  // swizzles to always use registers until generation of incorrect memory
5314  // operands can be fixed.
5315  src0_needs_reg = true;
5316  imms[imm_count++] = shuffle_mask;
5317  }
5318  } else {
5319  // 2 operand shuffle
5320  // A blend is more efficient than a general 32x4 shuffle; try it first.
5321  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchBlend(shuffle)) {
5322  opcode = kX64S16x8Blend;
5323  uint8_t blend_mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackBlend4(shuffle32x4);
5324  imms[imm_count++] = blend_mask;
5325  no_same_as_first = CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX);
5326  } else if (TryMatchShufps(shuffle32x4)) {
5327  opcode = kX64Shufps;
5328  uint8_t mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackShuffle4(shuffle32x4);
5329  imms[imm_count++] = mask;
5330  src1_needs_reg = true;
5331  no_same_as_first = IsSupported(AVX);
5332  } else {
5333  opcode = kX64S32x4Shuffle;
5334  no_same_as_first = true;
5335  // TODO(v8:9083): src0 and src1 is used by pshufd in codegen, which
5336  // requires memory to be 16-byte aligned, since we cannot guarantee that
5337  // yet, force using a register here.
5338  src0_needs_reg = true;
5339  src1_needs_reg = true;
5340  imms[imm_count++] = shuffle_mask;
5341  uint8_t blend_mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackBlend4(shuffle32x4);
5342  imms[imm_count++] = blend_mask;
5343  }
5344  }
5345  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatch16x8Shuffle(shuffle, shuffle16x8)) {
5346  uint8_t blend_mask;
5347  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchBlend(shuffle)) {
5348  opcode = kX64S16x8Blend;
5349  blend_mask = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackBlend8(shuffle16x8);
5350  imms[imm_count++] = blend_mask;
5351  no_same_as_first = CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX);
5352  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<8>(shuffle, &index)) {
5353  opcode = kX64S16x8Dup;
5354  src0_needs_reg = false;
5355  imms[imm_count++] = index;
5356  } else if (TryMatch16x8HalfShuffle(shuffle16x8, &blend_mask)) {
5357  opcode = is_swizzle ? kX64S16x8HalfShuffle1 : kX64S16x8HalfShuffle2;
5358  // Half-shuffles don't need DefineSameAsFirst or UseRegister(src0).
5359  no_same_as_first = true;
5360  src0_needs_reg = false;
5361  uint8_t mask_lo = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackShuffle4(shuffle16x8);
5362  uint8_t mask_hi = wasm::SimdShuffle::PackShuffle4(shuffle16x8 + 4);
5363  imms[imm_count++] = mask_lo;
5364  imms[imm_count++] = mask_hi;
5365  if (!is_swizzle) imms[imm_count++] = blend_mask;
5366  }
5367  } else if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchSplat<16>(shuffle, &index)) {
5368  opcode = kX64S8x16Dup;
5369  no_same_as_first = false;
5370  src0_needs_reg = true;
5371  imms[imm_count++] = index;
5372  } else if (TryMatchOneInputIsZeros(this, view, shuffle, &needs_swap)) {
5373  is_swizzle = true;
5374  // Swap zeros to input1
5375  if (needs_swap) {
5376  SwapShuffleInputs(view);
5377  for (int i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
5378  shuffle[i] ^= kSimd128Size;
5379  }
5380  }
5381  if (wasm::SimdShuffle::TryMatchByteToDwordZeroExtend(shuffle)) {
5382  opcode = kX64I32X4ShiftZeroExtendI8x16;
5383  no_same_as_first = true;
5384  src0_needs_reg = true;
5385  imms[imm_count++] = shuffle[0];
5386  } else {
5387  // If the most significant bit (bit 7) of each byte of the shuffle control
5388  // mask is set, then constant zero is written in the result byte. Input1
5389  // is zeros now, we can avoid using input1 by setting bit 7 of shuffle[i]
5390  // to 1.
5391  for (int i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
5392  if (shuffle[i] >= kSimd128Size) {
5393  shuffle[i] = 0x80;
5394  }
5395  }
5396  }
5397  }
5398  if (opcode == kX64I8x16Shuffle) {
5399  // Use same-as-first for general swizzle, but not shuffle.
5400  no_same_as_first = !is_swizzle;
5401  src0_needs_reg = !no_same_as_first;
5402  imms[imm_count++] = wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle);
5403  imms[imm_count++] = wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 4);
5404  imms[imm_count++] = wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 8);
5405  imms[imm_count++] = wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle + 12);
5406  temps[temp_count++] = g.TempSimd128Register();
5407  }
5408 
5409  // Use DefineAsRegister(node) and Use(src0) if we can without forcing an extra
5410  // move instruction in the CodeGenerator.
5411  OpIndex input0 = view.input(0);
5412  InstructionOperand dst =
5413  no_same_as_first ? g.DefineAsRegister(view) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(view);
5414  // TODO(v8:9198): Use src0_needs_reg when we have memory alignment for SIMD.
5415  // We only need a unique register for input0 if we use temp registers.
5416  InstructionOperand src0 =
5417  temp_count ? g.UseUniqueRegister(input0) : g.UseRegister(input0);
5418  USE(src0_needs_reg);
5419 
5420  int input_count = 0;
5421  InstructionOperand inputs[2 + kMaxImms + kMaxTemps];
5422  inputs[input_count++] = src0;
5423  if (!is_swizzle) {
5424  OpIndex input1 = view.input(1);
5425  // TODO(v8:9198): Use src1_needs_reg when we have memory alignment for SIMD.
5426  // We only need a unique register for input1 if we use temp registers.
5427  inputs[input_count++] =
5428  temp_count ? g.UseUniqueRegister(input1) : g.UseRegister(input1);
5429  USE(src1_needs_reg);
5430  }
5431  for (int i = 0; i < imm_count; ++i) {
5432  inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(imms[i]);
5433  }
5434  Emit(opcode, 1, &dst, input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
5435 }
5436 
5437 void InstructionSelector::VisitI8x16Swizzle(OpIndex node) {
5438  InstructionCode opcode = kX64I8x16Swizzle;
5439  const Simd128BinopOp& binop = Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(node);
5440  DCHECK_EQ(binop.input_count, 2);
5441  DCHECK(binop.kind == any_of(Simd128BinopOp::Kind::kI8x16Swizzle,
5442  Simd128BinopOp::Kind::kI8x16RelaxedSwizzle));
5443  bool relaxed = binop.kind == Simd128BinopOp::Kind::kI8x16RelaxedSwizzle;
5444  OpIndex left = binop.left();
5445  OpIndex right = binop.right();
5446 
5447  if (relaxed) {
5448  opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
5449  } else {
5450  std::array<uint8_t, kSimd128Size> imms;
5451  if (MatchSimd128Constant(this, right, &imms)) {
5452  // If the indices vector is a const, check if they are in range, or if the
5453  // top bit is set, then we can avoid the paddusb in the codegen and simply
5454  // emit a pshufb.
5455  opcode |=
5456  MiscField::encode(wasm::SimdSwizzle::AllInRangeOrTopBitSet(imms));
5457  }
5458  }
5459 
5460  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5461  Emit(opcode,
5462  IsSupported(AVX) ? g.DefineAsRegister(node) : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node),
5463  g.UseRegister(left), g.UseRegister(right));
5464 }
5465 
5466 namespace {
5467 void VisitRelaxedLaneSelect(InstructionSelector* selector, OpIndex node,
5468  InstructionCode code) {
5469  X64OperandGenerator g(selector);
5470  const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
5471  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 3);
5472  // pblendvb/blendvps/blendvpd copies src2 when mask is set, opposite from Wasm
5473  // semantics. Node's inputs are: mask, lhs, rhs (determined in
5474  // wasm-compiler.cc).
5475  if (selector->IsSupported(AVX)) {
5476  selector->Emit(code, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(2)),
5477  g.UseRegister(op.input(1)), g.UseRegister(op.input(0)));
5478  } else {
5479  // SSE4.1 pblendvb/blendvps/blendvpd requires xmm0 to hold the mask as an
5480  // implicit operand.
5481  selector->Emit(code, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(op.input(2)),
5482  g.UseRegister(op.input(1)), g.UseFixed(op.input(0), xmm0));
5483  }
5484 }
5485 } // namespace

5800 void InstructionSelector::VisitI64x2GtS(OpIndex node) {
5801  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5802  const Simd128BinopOp& op = Cast<Simd128BinopOp>(node);
5803  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 2);
5804  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
5805  Emit(kX64IGtS | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
5806  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
5807  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(op.left()),
5808  g.UseRegister(op.right()));
5809  } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_2)) {
5810  Emit(kX64IGtS | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
5811  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
5812  g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(op.left()),
5813  g.UseRegister(op.right()));
5814  } else {
5815  Emit(kX64IGtS | LaneSizeField::encode(kL64) |
5816  VectorLengthField::encode(kV128),
5817  g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseUniqueRegister(op.left()),
5818  g.UseUniqueRegister(op.right()));
5819  }
5820 }

5874 bool InstructionSelector::CanOptimizeF64x2PromoteLowF32x4(OpIndex node) {
5875  const Simd128UnaryOp& op = Cast<Opmask::kSimd128F64x2PromoteLowF32x4>(node);
5876  V<Simd128> input = op.input();
5877  return Is<Opmask::kSimd128LoadTransform64Zero>(input) &&
5878  CanCover(node, input);
5879 }
5880 
5881 void InstructionSelector::VisitF64x2PromoteLowF32x4(OpIndex node) {
5882  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
5883  const Simd128UnaryOp& op = Cast<Simd128UnaryOp>(node);
5884  DCHECK_EQ(op.input_count, 1);
5885  InstructionCode code = kX64F64x2PromoteLowF32x4;
5886  if (CanOptimizeF64x2PromoteLowF32x4(node)) {
5887  V<Simd128> input = op.input();
5888  const Simd128LoadTransformOp& load_transform =
5889  Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>(input);
5890  if (load_transform.load_kind.with_trap_handler) {
5891  code |= AccessModeField::encode(kMemoryAccessProtectedMemOutOfBounds);
5892  }
5893  // LoadTransforms cannot be eliminated, so they are visited even if
5894  // unused. Mark it as defined so that we don't visit it.
5895  MarkAsDefined(input);
5896  VisitLoad(node, input, code);
5897  return;
5898  }
5899 
5900  VisitRR(this, node, code);
5901 }

5977 // static
5978 MachineOperatorBuilder::Flags
5979 InstructionSelector::SupportedMachineOperatorFlags() {
5980  MachineOperatorBuilder::Flags flags =
5981  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32ShiftIsSafe |
5982  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Ctz | MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Ctz |
5983  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Rol | MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Rol |
5984  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Select |
5985  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Select;
5986  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(POPCNT)) {
5987  flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord32Popcnt |
5988  MachineOperatorBuilder::kWord64Popcnt;
5989  }
5990  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(SSE4_1)) {
5991  flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundDown |
5992  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundDown |
5993  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundUp |
5994  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundUp |
5995  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTruncate |
5996  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTruncate |
5997  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat32RoundTiesEven |
5998  MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat64RoundTiesEven;
5999  }
6000  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(F16C)) {
6001  flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat16;
6002  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX)) {
6003  flags |= MachineOperatorBuilder::kFloat16RawBitsConversion;
6004  }
6005  }
6006  return flags;
6007 }

6010 MachineOperatorBuilder::AlignmentRequirements
6011 InstructionSelector::AlignmentRequirements() {
6012  return MachineOperatorBuilder::AlignmentRequirements::
6013  FullUnalignedAccessSupport();
6014 }
